{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KGw8nEdHk13o4MWxVkxsQU","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Iteration 11 Failure Analysis\n     2→\n     3→## Failure: CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\n     4→\n     5→**Expected:** `CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM`\n     6→**Got:** `CHLEBEK`\n     7→\n     8→**Input structure (key lines):**\n     9→```\n    10→idx 0:  Lato | Dania główne                      ← book category header (\"Summer | Main dishes\")\n    11→idx 1:  CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM           ← actual recipe title (5 words, ALL_CAPS)\n    12→idx 2:  WARZYWA I BOCZEK                         ← section header (\"Vegetables and Bacon\")\n    13→idx 3:  500 g strączków zielonego groszku        ← ingredient (starts with number)\n    14→idx 4:  1 żółta papryka                          ← ingredient\n    15→...\n    16→idx 8:  CHLEBEK                                  ← section header (\"Bread\")\n    17→idx 9:  500 g mąki                               ← ingredient (starts with number)\n    18→...\n    19→```\n    20→\n    21→---\n    22→\n    23→## Root Cause: False Positive in Bilingual Title Detection\n    24→\n    25→### What the bilingual detection is supposed to do\n    26→\n    27→The bilingual detection at lines 409–431 targets a specific page layout: a **mixed-case title in language A** at position 0, followed immediately by an **ALL_CAPS romanization/translation** at positions 1–2. It suppresses the ALL_CAPS candidate from the threshold calculation so the original mixed-case title can win.\n    28→\n    29→### Why it misfires here\n    30→\n    31→`prePos0` = `\"Lato | Dania główne\"` — This line passes the check: it is at position 0 and is not ALL_CAPS.\n    32→\n    33→However, `\"Lato | Dania główne\"` is not a recipe title at all. It is a **book chapter header** meaning \"Summer | Main dishes\". It marks the section of the cookbook, not a recipe.\n    34→\n    35→`nearbyAllCaps` = candidates at positions 1–2:\n    36→- `\"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\"` (position 1)\n    37→- `\"WARZYWA I BOCZEK\"` (position 2)\n    38→\n    39→The algorithm then computes cosine similarity between `\"Lato | Dania główne\"` and each of these. Both are Polish food-related texts. In a multilingual embedding space, food-domain terms share enough semantic neighbourhood that the similarity of `\"Summer | Main dishes\"` to `\"BREAD WITH VEGETABLES AND BACON\"` can exceed the 0.4 threshold.\n    40→\n    41→When one or both are identified as `translationCandidates`, the filter:\n    42→```javascript\n    43→scoredForThreshold = scored.filter((s) => {\n    44→  const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n    45→  return !translationCandidates.some((t) => sLower.startsWith(t.text.toLowerCase()));\n    46→});\n    47→```\n    48→also removes the 2-line join `\"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM WARZYWA I BOCZEK\"` (it starts with the suppressed text). The result is that **all longer ALL_CAPS candidates anchored at position 1 are purged from `scoredForThreshold`** — and therefore from `selected`.\n    49→\n    50→### The cascade after suppression\n    51→\n    52→With `\"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\"` absent from `selected`:\n    53→\n    54→1. **Prefix removal doesn't fire** (lines 458–466). The guard is `if (firstStructuralHeading && selected.some((s) => s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text))`. `firstStructuralHeading` may point to `\"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\"` from `rawScored` (embedding quality), but it is not in `selected`, so the condition is false. `\"CHLEBEK\"` is never removed as a prefix.\n    55→\n    56→2. **Pre-dedup section filter cannot act** (lines 506–523). The filter correctly identifies `\"CHLEBEK\"` (position 8) as an ALL_CAPS candidate followed by an ingredient line (`\"500 g mąki\"` starts with a number). But the filter only removes `\"CHLEBEK\"` when a longer candidate containing it exists in `selected`. Since `\"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\"` was suppressed, `hasLongerParent = false`. `\"CHLEBEK\"` survives.\n    57→\n    58→3. **Dedup rule** (shorter wins) has nothing to act on — `\"CHLEBEK\"` is the only ALL_CAPS survivor in the upper portion of the document.\n    59→\n    60→4. **Multi-title guard** sees `\"CHLEBEK\"` as the first (or only) surviving ALL_CAPS candidate and returns it.\n    61→\n    62→Result: `\"CHLEBEK\"` — the bread sub-section header — is returned instead of the recipe title.\n    63→\n    64→---\n    65→\n    66→## Why Previous Fix Was Insufficient\n    67→\n    68→Iteration 10 identified the pre-dedup section filter (lines 506–523) and the prefix removal step (lines 458–466) as mechanisms to handle the `\"CHLEBEK\"` / `\"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\"` conflict. Both mechanisms are correct **when the full title is present in `selected`**. The iteration 10 fix correctly handles the 25-candidate cap issue (the full title now has 5 words, fitting the `wordCount <= 5` priority tier). But neither fix anticipated the bilingual detection suppressing the full title before either mechanism gets a chance to act.\n    69→\n    70→---\n    71→\n    72→## Common Themes\n    73→\n    74→### 1. Book category headers are indistinguishable from recipe titles by position\n    75→\n    76→`\"Lato | Dania główne\"` (\"Summer | Main dishes\") appears at position 0 and passes all hard filters. The algorithm has no concept of \"chapter header\" vs \"recipe title\". The bilingual detection triggers on it as if it were a foreign-language recipe title, suppressing the real title two lines below.\n    77→\n    78→### 2. Bilingual detection uses a 0.4 similarity threshold that is too permissive for food content\n    79→\n    80→The bilingual detection was designed for clearly-paired translations (e.g., Korean title → ALL_CAPS romanization). The 0.4 threshold is calibrated for cross-lingual translation, but within Polish food text, `\"Summer | Main dishes\"` and `\"BREAD WITH VEGETABLES AND BACON\"` may share enough domain vocabulary to exceed it. This causes the correction mechanism to fire on a completely unrelated pair.\n    81→\n    82→### 3. Cascading dependency on full title presence\n    83→\n    84→Multiple downstream safety mechanisms (prefix removal at line 458, pre-dedup filter at line 506) are gated on the full title being present in `selected`. They are not independently robust — they share the same precondition. One upstream suppression (bilingual detection) disables both simultaneously, leaving no fallback.\n    85→\n    86→### 4. Section headers as recipe title candidates\n    87→\n    88→`\"WARZYWA I BOCZEK\"` and `\"CHLEBEK\"` are cookbook sub-section headers (ingredient groups for the two components of the recipe). They resemble recipe titles structurally: short, ALL_CAPS, Polish food words. The algorithm cannot distinguish them from standalone recipe titles without knowing the document structure. The document structure (each section header immediately followed by its ingredient list) is the necessary signal, and while the multi-title guard and pre-dedup filter attempt to use it, both are blocked by the earlier suppression.\n    89→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e5c8568-eb2f-4e0e-8771-787e6907f7e7","uuid":"4bee17b5-9209-42b4-935c-ba7a8534b9bc","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/docs/11-023af39/feedback.md","content":"# Iteration 11 Failure Analysis\n\n## Failure: CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\n\n**Expected:** `CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM`\n**Got:** `CHLEBEK`\n\n**Input structure (key lines):**\n```\nidx 0:  Lato | Dania główne                      ← book category header (\"Summer | Main dishes\")\nidx 1:  CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM           ← actual recipe title (5 words, ALL_CAPS)\nidx 2:  WARZYWA I BOCZEK                         ← section header (\"Vegetables and Bacon\")\nidx 3:  500 g strączków zielonego groszku        ← ingredient (starts with number)\nidx 4:  1 żółta papryka                          ← ingredient\n...\nidx 8:  CHLEBEK                                  ← section header (\"Bread\")\nidx 9:  500 g mąki                               ← ingredient (starts with number)\n...\n```\n\n---\n\n## Root Cause: False Positive in Bilingual Title Detection\n\n### What the bilingual detection is supposed to do\n\nThe bilingual detection at lines 409–431 targets a specific page layout: a **mixed-case title in language A** at position 0, followed immediately by an **ALL_CAPS romanization/translation** at positions 1–2. It suppresses the ALL_CAPS candidate from the threshold calculation so the original mixed-case title can win.\n\n### Why it misfires here\n\n`prePos0` = `\"Lato | Dania główne\"` — This line passes the check: it is at position 0 and is not ALL_CAPS.\n\nHowever, `\"Lato | Dania główne\"` is not a recipe title at all. It is a **book chapter header** meaning \"Summer | Main dishes\". It marks the section of the cookbook, not a recipe.\n\n`nearbyAllCaps` = candidates at positions 1–2:\n- `\"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\"` (position 1)\n- `\"WARZYWA I BOCZEK\"` (position 2)\n\nThe algorithm then computes cosine similarity between `\"Lato | Dania główne\"` and each of these. Both are Polish food-related texts. In a multilingual embedding space, food-domain terms share enough semantic neighbourhood that the similarity of `\"Summer | Main dishes\"` to `\"BREAD WITH VEGETABLES AND BACON\"` can exceed the 0.4 threshold.\n\nWhen one or both are identified as `translationCandidates`, the filter:\n```javascript\nscoredForThreshold = scored.filter((s) => {\n  const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n  return !translationCandidates.some((t) => sLower.startsWith(t.text.toLowerCase()));\n});\n```\nalso removes the 2-line join `\"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM WARZYWA I BOCZEK\"` (it starts with the suppressed text). The result is that **all longer ALL_CAPS candidates anchored at position 1 are purged from `scoredForThreshold`** — and therefore from `selected`.\n\n### The cascade after suppression\n\nWith `\"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\"` absent from `selected`:\n\n1. **Prefix removal doesn't fire** (lines 458–466). The guard is `if (firstStructuralHeading && selected.some((s) => s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text))`. `firstStructuralHeading` may point to `\"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\"` from `rawScored` (embedding quality), but it is not in `selected`, so the condition is false. `\"CHLEBEK\"` is never removed as a prefix.\n\n2. **Pre-dedup section filter cannot act** (lines 506–523). The filter correctly identifies `\"CHLEBEK\"` (position 8) as an ALL_CAPS candidate followed by an ingredient line (`\"500 g mąki\"` starts with a number). But the filter only removes `\"CHLEBEK\"` when a longer candidate containing it exists in `selected`. Since `\"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\"` was suppressed, `hasLongerParent = false`. `\"CHLEBEK\"` survives.\n\n3. **Dedup rule** (shorter wins) has nothing to act on — `\"CHLEBEK\"` is the only ALL_CAPS survivor in the upper portion of the document.\n\n4. **Multi-title guard** sees `\"CHLEBEK\"` as the first (or only) surviving ALL_CAPS candidate and returns it.\n\nResult: `\"CHLEBEK\"` — the bread sub-section header — is returned instead of the recipe title.\n\n---\n\n## Why Previous Fix Was Insufficient\n\nIteration 10 identified the pre-dedup section filter (lines 506–523) and the prefix removal step (lines 458–466) as mechanisms to handle the `\"CHLEBEK\"` / `\"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\"` conflict. Both mechanisms are correct **when the full title is present in `selected`**. The iteration 10 fix correctly handles the 25-candidate cap issue (the full title now has 5 words, fitting the `wordCount <= 5` priority tier). But neither fix anticipated the bilingual detection suppressing the full title before either mechanism gets a chance to act.\n\n---\n\n## Common Themes\n\n### 1. Book category headers are indistinguishable from recipe titles by position\n\n`\"Lato | Dania główne\"` (\"Summer | Main dishes\") appears at position 0 and passes all hard filters. The algorithm has no concept of \"chapter header\" vs \"recipe title\". The bilingual detection triggers on it as if it were a foreign-language recipe title, suppressing the real title two lines below.\n\n### 2. Bilingual detection uses a 0.4 similarity threshold that is too permissive for food content\n\nThe bilingual detection was designed for clearly-paired translations (e.g., Korean title → ALL_CAPS romanization). The 0.4 threshold is calibrated for cross-lingual translation, but within Polish food text, `\"Summer | Main dishes\"` and `\"BREAD WITH VEGETABLES AND BACON\"` may share enough domain vocabulary to exceed it. This causes the correction mechanism to fire on a completely unrelated pair.\n\n### 3. Cascading dependency on full title presence\n\nMultiple downstream safety mechanisms (prefix removal at line 458, pre-dedup filter at line 506) are gated on the full title being present in `selected`. They are not independently robust — they share the same precondition. One upstream suppression (bilingual detection) disables both simultaneously, leaving no fallback.\n\n### 4. Section headers as recipe title candidates\n\n`\"WARZYWA I BOCZEK\"` and `\"CHLEBEK\"` are cookbook sub-section headers (ingredient groups for the two components of the recipe). They resemble recipe titles structurally: short, ALL_CAPS, Polish food words. The algorithm cannot distinguish them from standalone recipe titles without knowing the document structure. The document structure (each section header immediately followed by its ingredient list) is the necessary signal, and while the multi-title guard and pre-dedup filter attempt to use it, both are blocked by the earlier suppression.\n","numLines":89,"startLine":1,"totalLines":89}}}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01TQXJkr6KyhQQFVhw1Fhszr","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Title Extraction\n     3→ * Extracts potential recipe title from OCR text using heuristics or semantic embeddings\n     4→ */\n     5→\n     6→import { cosineSimilarity } from \"./embeddings\";\n     7→\n     8→export type EmbedFn = (text: string) => Promise<Array<number>>;\n     9→\n    10→const TITLE_REFERENCE =\n    11→  \"recipe name, dish title, name of the food, nazwa przepisu, nazwa dania\";\n    12→const HEADER_REFERENCE =\n    13→  \"ingredients list, cooking directions, section heading, składniki, przygotowanie, sposób wykonania\";\n    14→const NOISE_REFERENCE =\n    15→  \"page number, table of contents, book footer, garbled text\";\n    16→\n    17→/**\n    18→ * Measurement units commonly found in ingredient lists\n    19→ */\n    20→const MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS = [\n    21→  \"cup\",\n    22→  \"cups\",\n    23→  \"tbsp\",\n    24→  \"tsp\",\n    25→  \"tablespoon\",\n    26→  \"teaspoon\",\n    27→  \"oz\",\n    28→  \"lb\",\n    29→  \"gram\",\n    30→  \"grams\",\n    31→  \"kg\",\n    32→  \"ml\",\n    33→  \"liter\",\n    34→  \"pinch\",\n    35→  \"dash\",\n    36→  \"handful\",\n    37→];\n    38→\n    39→/**\n    40→ * Patterns that identify recipe metadata lines (not titles)\n    41→ */\n    42→const METADATA_PATTERNS = [\n    43→  /^(SERVES?|MAKES?|YIELDS?)\\b/i,\n    44→  /^(PREP(ARATION)?|COOK(ING)?|PROOF|RISING|FERMENTATION|REST(ING)?)\\s*(AND\\s*)?(COOK(ING)?)?\\s*TIME/i,\n    45→  /^SAMPLE\\s+SCHEDULE\\b/i,\n    46→  /^BULK\\s+FERMENTATION\\b/i,\n    47→  /^(THIS\\s+RECIPE\\s+)?MAKES\\b/i,\n    48→  // Polish serving-size patterns: \"NA 3 PAPRYKI\", \"NA OKOŁO 1 KG\", \"DLA 4 OSÓB\"\n    49→  /^NA\\s+(\\d|OKOŁO)\\b/i,\n    50→  /^DLA\\s+\\d/i,\n    51→  // Time-unit metadata: any line containing \"N MIN\" or \"N GODZ\" is prep/cook/rest time,\n    52→  // regardless of OCR-corrupted prefix (catches PRZYGOTOWANTE, GOTOMANTE, etc.)\n    53→  /\\b\\d+\\s*MIN\\b/i,\n    54→  /\\b\\d+\\s*GODZ/i,\n    55→];\n    56→\n    57→/**\n    58→ * Single-word non-title words — standalone OCR fragments unlikely to be recipe titles\n    59→ */\n    60→const NON_TITLE_WORDS = new Set([\n    61→  \"the\", \"and\", \"for\", \"but\", \"not\", \"you\", \"all\", \"can\", \"are\", \"was\",\n    62→  \"has\", \"his\", \"her\", \"its\", \"our\", \"who\", \"how\", \"may\", \"new\", \"now\",\n    63→  \"old\", \"see\", \"way\", \"did\", \"get\", \"let\", \"say\", \"she\", \"too\", \"use\",\n    64→  \"buns\", \"with\",\n    65→]);\n    66→\n    67→function looksLikeIngredient(line: string): boolean {\n    68→  const lowerLine = line.toLowerCase();\n    69→  return MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS.some((pattern) => lowerLine.includes(pattern));\n    70→}\n    71→\n    72→function startsWithNumber(line: string): boolean {\n    73→  return /^\\s*\\d/.test(line);\n    74→}\n    75→\n    76→function isAllCaps(line: string): boolean {\n    77→  const letters = line.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\");\n    78→  return letters.length > 0 && letters === letters.toUpperCase();\n    79→}\n    80→\n    81→function looksLikeMetadata(text: string): boolean {\n    82→  return METADATA_PATTERNS.some((pattern) => pattern.test(text.trim()));\n    83→}\n    84→\n    85→function isLikelyGarbled(text: string): boolean {\n    86→  const letters = text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\");\n    87→  if (letters.length < 2) return true;\n    88→\n    89→  // Check vowel ratio — English/Polish text typically has 30–50% vowels\n    90→  const vowels = letters.replace(/[^aeiouAEIOUyYąęóĄĘÓ]/g, \"\").length;\n    91→  const vowelRatio = vowels / letters.length;\n    92→  if (vowelRatio < 0.15 || vowelRatio > 0.85) return true;\n    93→\n    94→  // Single orphaned word ≤3 letters that isn't a common word\n    95→  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n    96→  const COMMON_SHORT = new Set([\n    97→    \"the\", \"and\", \"for\", \"but\", \"not\", \"you\", \"all\", \"can\", \"had\", \"her\",\n    98→    \"was\", \"one\", \"our\", \"out\", \"are\", \"has\", \"his\", \"how\", \"its\", \"may\",\n    99→    \"new\", \"now\", \"old\", \"see\", \"way\", \"who\", \"did\", \"get\", \"let\", \"say\",\n   100→    \"she\", \"too\", \"use\",\n   101→  ]);\n   102→  if (words.length === 1 && letters.length <= 3 && !COMMON_SHORT.has(text.trim().toLowerCase())) {\n   103→    return true;\n   104→  }\n   105→\n   106→  // Recipe titles never start with a lowercase letter\n   107→  if (/^[a-z]/.test(text.trim())) {\n   108→    return true;\n   109→  }\n   110→\n   111→  // Mid-text sentence boundary (\". \" followed by a letter) — body text fragment spliced from multiple sentences\n   112→  const trimmed = text.trim();\n   113→  if (/\\.\\s+[a-zA-Z]/.test(trimmed) && !trimmed.endsWith(\")\")) {\n   114→    return true;\n   115→  }\n   116→\n   117→  // Multi-word candidate containing a garbled OCR fragment: a short lowercase word that isn't a known short word\n   118→  if (words.length >= 2) {\n   119→    const commonShort2 = new Set([\n   120→      \"a\", \"i\", \"of\", \"or\", \"to\", \"in\", \"on\", \"is\", \"it\", \"an\",\n   121→      \"as\", \"at\", \"by\", \"do\", \"go\", \"if\", \"no\", \"so\", \"up\", \"we\",\n   122→      \"w\", \"z\",  // Polish prepositions\n   123→    ]);\n   124→    const hasGarbledWord = words.some(\n   125→      (w) =>\n   126→        /^[a-z]/.test(w) &&\n   127→        w.replace(/[^a-z]/g, \"\").length <= 2 &&\n   128→        !commonShort2.has(w.toLowerCase())\n   129→    );\n   130→    if (hasGarbledWord) {\n   131→      return true;\n   132→    }\n   133→  }\n   134→\n   135→  return false;\n   136→}\n   137→\n   138→function passesHardFilters(text: string): boolean {\n   139→  if (text.length < 3 || text.length > 80) return false;\n   140→  if (looksLikeIngredient(text)) return false;\n   141→  if (startsWithNumber(text)) return false;\n   142→  if (looksLikeMetadata(text)) return false;\n   143→  if (isLikelyGarbled(text)) return false;\n   144→  // Single-word non-title fragments\n   145→  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n   146→  if (words.length === 1 && NON_TITLE_WORDS.has(text.trim().toLowerCase())) return false;\n   147→  return true;\n   148→}\n   149→\n   150→/**\n   151→ * Detect initial burst of short garbled lines.\n   152→ * Returns the index of the first non-garbled or long line.\n   153→ */\n   154→function findBurstEnd(lines: Array<{ text: string }>): number {\n   155→  let i = 0;\n   156→  while (i < lines.length && lines[i].text.length < 20 && isLikelyGarbled(lines[i].text)) {\n   157→    i++;\n   158→  }\n   159→  return i;\n   160→}\n   161→\n   162→function wordCount(text: string): number {\n   163→  return text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.length > 0).length;\n   164→}\n   165→\n   166→/**\n   167→ * Build candidate strings from lines: single lines plus multi-line joins (2-3 consecutive).\n   168→ * Skips initial burst of short garbled lines. Scans all remaining lines. Caps at 25.\n   169→ */\n   170→export type CandidateOrigin = \"single\" | \"2-line\" | \"3-line\";\n   171→\n   172→function buildCandidates(\n   173→  lines: Array<string>\n   174→): Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }> {\n   175→  const nonEmptyLines: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n   176→\n   177→  for (let i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {\n   178→    const trimmed = lines[i].trim();\n   179→    if (trimmed.length > 0) {\n   180→      nonEmptyLines.push({ text: trimmed, index: i });\n   181→    }\n   182→  }\n   183→\n   184→  const burstEnd = findBurstEnd(nonEmptyLines);\n   185→\n   186→  // Pre-merge continuation lines: a line starting with /&+:( is never a standalone title.\n   187→  // Merge it into the preceding line so the complete title enters the pool as a single candidate,\n   188→  // avoiding the fragile chain of conditions required by the downstream join survival logic.\n   189→  // Limitation: only one continuation line per preceding line is merged. Titles split across\n   190→  // three or more lines with continuation tokens (rare in practice) are not handled here —\n   191→  // the downstream 2-line and 3-line join candidates cover those cases instead.\n   192→  const mergedLines: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n   193→  for (let i = burstEnd; i < nonEmptyLines.length; i++) {\n   194→    const line = nonEmptyLines[i];\n   195→    if (i + 1 < nonEmptyLines.length) {\n   196→      const nextText = nonEmptyLines[i + 1].text;\n   197→      if (/^[/&+:(]/.test(nextText)) {\n   198→        mergedLines.push({ text: `${line.text} ${nextText}`, index: line.index });\n   199→        i++;\n   200→        continue;\n   201→      }\n   202→    }\n   203→    mergedLines.push(line);\n   204→  }\n   205→\n   206→  const candidates: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }> = [];\n   207→  const seen = new Set<string>();\n   208→\n   209→  for (let i = 0; i < mergedLines.length; i++) {\n   210→    const line = mergedLines[i];\n   211→\n   212→    // Single line\n   213→    if (passesHardFilters(line.text)) {\n   214→      const norm = line.text.toLowerCase();\n   215→      if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n   216→        seen.add(norm);\n   217→        candidates.push({ text: line.text, position: line.index, origin: \"single\" });\n   218→      }\n   219→    }\n   220→\n   221→    // 2-line join\n   222→    if (i + 1 < mergedLines.length) {\n   223→      const joined2 = `${line.text} ${mergedLines[i + 1].text}`;\n   224→      if (passesHardFilters(joined2)) {\n   225→        const norm = joined2.toLowerCase();\n   226→        if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n   227→          seen.add(norm);\n   228→          candidates.push({ text: joined2, position: line.index, origin: \"2-line\" });\n   229→        }\n   230→      }\n   231→    }\n   232→\n   233→    // 3-line join\n   234→    if (i + 2 < mergedLines.length) {\n   235→      const joined3 = `${line.text} ${mergedLines[i + 1].text} ${mergedLines[i + 2].text}`;\n   236→      if (passesHardFilters(joined3)) {\n   237→        const norm = joined3.toLowerCase();\n   238→        if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n   239→          seen.add(norm);\n   240→          candidates.push({ text: joined3, position: line.index, origin: \"3-line\" });\n   241→        }\n   242→      }\n   243→    }\n   244→  }\n   245→\n   246→  // Pre-filter to 25 before embedding calls: prefer ALL_CAPS and short candidates.\n   247→  // Position-based scoring handles final ranking.\n   248→  if (candidates.length > 25) {\n   249→    const prioritized = candidates.slice().sort((a, b) => {\n   250→      const aAllCaps = isAllCaps(a.text) ? 0 : 1;\n   251→      const bAllCaps = isAllCaps(b.text) ? 0 : 1;\n   252→      if (aAllCaps !== bAllCaps) return aAllCaps - bAllCaps;\n   253→      const aShort = wordCount(a.text) <= 5 ? 0 : 1;\n   254→      const bShort = wordCount(b.text) <= 5 ? 0 : 1;\n   255→      return aShort - bShort;\n   256→    });\n   257→    return prioritized.slice(0, 25);\n   258→  }\n   259→\n   260→  return candidates;\n   261→}\n   262→\n   263→// Module-level cache for reference embeddings\n   264→let cachedTitleRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\n   265→let cachedHeaderRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\n   266→let cachedNoiseRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\n   267→\n   268→export function _resetEmbeddingCacheForTests(): void {\n   269→  cachedTitleRefEmbedding = null;\n   270→  cachedHeaderRefEmbedding = null;\n   271→  cachedNoiseRefEmbedding = null;\n   272→}\n   273→\n   274→export async function extractTitleWithEmbeddings(\n   275→  text: string,\n   276→  embed: EmbedFn\n   277→): Promise<string | undefined> {\n   278→  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) {\n   279→    return undefined;\n   280→  }\n   281→\n   282→  const lines = text.split(\"\\n\");\n   283→  const candidates = buildCandidates(lines);\n   284→\n   285→  if (candidates.length === 0) {\n   286→    return undefined;\n   287→  }\n   288→\n   289→  // Cache reference embeddings\n   290→  if (!cachedTitleRefEmbedding) {\n   291→    cachedTitleRefEmbedding = await embed(TITLE_REFERENCE);\n   292→  }\n   293→  if (!cachedHeaderRefEmbedding) {\n   294→    cachedHeaderRefEmbedding = await embed(HEADER_REFERENCE);\n   295→  }\n   296→  if (!cachedNoiseRefEmbedding) {\n   297→    cachedNoiseRefEmbedding = await embed(NOISE_REFERENCE);\n   298→  }\n   299→\n   300→  // Find ALL_CAPS candidates with ≥2 words where every significant word has ≥4 alpha letters.\n   301→  // Insignificant tokens (≤1 alpha letter: \"/\", \"&\", \"+\", \":\", \"D)\", etc.) are filtered before\n   302→  // the check so that multi-line joins with continuation punctuation still qualify.\n   303→  const isStructuralHeading = (c: { text: string }): boolean => {\n   304→    if (!isAllCaps(c.text) || wordCount(c.text) < 2) return false;\n   305→    const sigWords = c.text.trim().split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length > 1);\n   306→    return sigWords.length >= 2 && sigWords.every((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n   307→  };\n   308→\n   309→  // Pass 1: compute rawScore for all candidates (embedding quality signal)\n   310→  const rawScored: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin; rawScore: number; embedding: Array<number> }> = [];\n   311→  for (const candidate of candidates) {\n   312→    const embedding = await embed(candidate.text);\n   313→    const titleSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedTitleRefEmbedding);\n   314→    const headerSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedHeaderRefEmbedding);\n   315→    const noiseSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedNoiseRefEmbedding);\n   316→    const rawScore = titleSim - Math.max(headerSim, noiseSim);\n   317→    rawScored.push({ text: candidate.text, position: candidate.position, origin: candidate.origin, rawScore, embedding });\n   318→  }\n   319→\n   320→  // Select baseHeading by embedding quality (rawScore), not position.\n   321→  // This prevents OCR-garbled fragments from claiming the structural heading slot.\n   322→  const structuralCandidates = rawScored.filter((s) => isStructuralHeading(s));\n   323→\n   324→  // Penalize structural headings with truncated OCR words:\n   325→  // if \"FRON\" appears and another heading has \"SAFFRON\", \"FRON\" is likely garbled.\n   326→  for (const sc of structuralCandidates) {\n   327→    const sigWords = sc.text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n   328→    for (const other of structuralCandidates) {\n   329→      if (other === sc) continue;\n   330→      const otherSigWords = other.text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n   331→      const hasTruncation = sigWords.some((w) =>\n   332→        otherSigWords.some((ow) => ow !== w && ow.length > w.length && ow.endsWith(w))\n   333→      );\n   334→      if (hasTruncation) {\n   335→        sc.rawScore = -1.0;  // Hard disqualification — truncated OCR artifact\n   336→        break;\n   337→      }\n   338→    }\n   339→  }\n   340→\n   341→  const bestStructural = structuralCandidates.length > 0\n   342→    ? structuralCandidates.reduce((a, b) => {\n   343→        const scoreDiff = a.rawScore - b.rawScore;\n   344→        if (Math.abs(scoreDiff) > 0.03) return scoreDiff > 0 ? a : b;\n   345→        // Tiebreak: single-line origin beats multi-line joins (avoids conflating two separate headings)\n   346→        if (a.origin === \"single\" && b.origin !== \"single\") return a;\n   347→        if (b.origin === \"single\" && a.origin !== \"single\") return b;\n   348→        // Tiebreak: more words (more specific) → better\n   349→        const wcDiff = wordCount(b.text) - wordCount(a.text);\n   350→        if (wcDiff !== 0) return wcDiff > 0 ? b : a;\n   351→        // Tiebreak: earlier position → better\n   352→        return a.position < b.position ? a : b;\n   353→      })\n   354→    : null;\n   355→  const baseHeading = bestStructural ?? undefined;\n   356→\n   357→  // When the best structural heading has a continuation on the next line introduced by a\n   358→  // punctuation token (/, &, +, :, or parenthesis), prefer the longer 2-line join as the\n   359→  // complete heading. E.g. \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\" + \"/ COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\".\n   360→  // Guard: the remainder after the prefix must start with a continuation character to avoid\n   361→  // merging two separate consecutive recipe titles (FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS stays separate\n   362→  // from FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS because \"FINNISH\" does not start with a continuation token).\n   363→  const firstStructuralHeading = baseHeading && (\n   364→    rawScored.find((c) => {\n   365→      if (!isStructuralHeading(c)) return false;\n   366→      const hLower = baseHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n   367→      const cLower = c.text.toLowerCase();\n   368→      return cLower.startsWith(hLower + \" \") && /^[/&+:(]/.test(cLower.slice(hLower.length + 1));\n   369→    }) ?? baseHeading\n   370→  );\n   371→\n   372→  // Pass 2: apply bonuses\n   373→  const scored: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin; score: number; rawScore: number; baseScore: number; thresholdScore: number }> = rawScored.map((rs) => {\n   374→    // Position factor: multiplicative tiebreaker — amplifies existing signal, doesn't replace it\n   375→    const relativePosition = rs.position / lines.length;\n   376→    const positionFactor = relativePosition < 0.5\n   377→      ? 1.0 + 0.12 * (1 - relativePosition * 2)\n   378→      : 1.0;\n   379→\n   380→    // ALL_CAPS bonus: recipe books use ALL_CAPS for titles and section headings\n   381→    const allCapsBonus = isAllCaps(rs.text) && rs.text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4\n   382→      ? 0.08\n   383→      : 0;\n   384→\n   385→    // Structural heading bonus: best ALL_CAPS heading (or its continuation join) is almost always the recipe title\n   386→    const structuralBonus = firstStructuralHeading && rs.text === firstStructuralHeading.text ? 0.10 : 0;\n   387→\n   388→    // thresholdScore excludes structural bonus so the bonus doesn't inflate the threshold\n   389→    // and prevent equally-valid structural headings from passing on multi-recipe pages.\n   390→    const thresholdScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus;\n   391→    // baseScore excludes position factor — used for diagnostics and ranking\n   392→    const baseScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n   393→    const score = rs.rawScore * positionFactor + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n   394→    return { text: rs.text, position: rs.position, origin: rs.origin, score, rawScore: rs.rawScore, baseScore, thresholdScore };\n   395→  });\n   396→\n   397→  if (scored.length === 0) {\n   398→    return undefined;\n   399→  }\n   400→\n   401→  // --- Pre-threshold bilingual title detection ---\n   402→  // When a mixed-case candidate at position 0 is followed by an ALL_CAPS candidate\n   403→  // at position ≤ 2 that is semantically similar to it, this is a bilingual recipe\n   404→  // page (e.g., Polish title + ALL_CAPS Korean romanization). Suppress confirmed\n   405→  // translation candidates before computing threshold so their bonuses don't inflate\n   406→  // the threshold beyond the mixed-case title's reach.\n   407→  // Note: we check position ≤ 2 (local proximity), not global ALL_CAPS count, so\n   408→  // section headers later in the document (SKŁADNIKI, WARZYWA, etc.) are irrelevant.\n   409→  let scoredForThreshold = scored;\n   410→  const prePos0 = scored.find((s) => s.position === 0 && !isAllCaps(s.text));\n   411→  if (prePos0) {\n   412→    const nearbyAllCaps = scored.filter(\n   413→      (s) => isAllCaps(s.text) && s.position >= 1 && s.position <= 2\n   414→    );\n   415→    const pos0Embedding = rawScored.find((r) => r.text === prePos0.text)?.embedding;\n   416→    if (pos0Embedding && nearbyAllCaps.length > 0) {\n   417→      const translationCandidates = nearbyAllCaps.filter((cap) => {\n   418→        const capEmbedding = rawScored.find((r) => r.text === cap.text)?.embedding;\n   419→        if (!capEmbedding) return false;\n   420→        return cosineSimilarity(pos0Embedding, capEmbedding) > 0.4;\n   421→      });\n   422→      if (translationCandidates.length > 0) {\n   423→        // Also suppress multi-line joins that start with the translation text\n   424→        // (e.g. \"PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM Ingredients\" starts with \"PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM\")\n   425→        scoredForThreshold = scored.filter((s) => {\n   426→          const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n   427→          return !translationCandidates.some((t) => sLower.startsWith(t.text.toLowerCase()));\n   428→        });\n   429→      }\n   430→    }\n   431→  }\n   432→\n   433→  // Use thresholdScore (excludes structural bonus) so the structural bonus doesn't inflate\n   434→  // the threshold and block equally-valid headings on multi-recipe pages.\n   435→  const bestThresholdScore = Math.max(...scoredForThreshold.map((s) => s.thresholdScore));\n   436→  const threshold = Math.max(0.08, bestThresholdScore * 0.7);\n   437→\n   438→  // Filter candidates above threshold\n   439→  let selected = scoredForThreshold.filter((s) => s.score >= threshold);\n   440→\n   441→  // Empty-pool fallback: when threshold filtering discards every candidate,\n   442→  // the hard filters' structural verdict should not be overruled by weak\n   443→  // embedding differentiation. Return the best positional candidate.\n   444→  if (selected.length === 0 && scored.length > 0) {\n   445→    const fallback = scored\n   446→      .slice()\n   447→      .sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position || b.score - a.score);\n   448→    selected = [fallback[0]];\n   449→  }\n   450→\n   451→  // Remove word-boundary prefixes of firstStructuralHeading when the heading itself survived\n   452→  // the threshold. Cases:\n   453→  //   ARAYES case:  firstStructuralHeading = \"ARAYES SHRAK\" (2-word join qualifies; \"ARAYES\"\n   454→  //     alone = 1 word, so it never qualified). Filter removes \"ARAYES\" so dedup keeps the join.\n   455→  //   SAFFRON case: baseHeading was the partial line; continuation logic above upgraded\n   456→  //     firstStructuralHeading to the full join. Filter removes the partial so dedup keeps join.\n   457→  // Safety: only fires when the complete heading itself is in selected (passed the threshold).\n   458→  if (firstStructuralHeading && selected.some((s) => s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text)) {\n   459→    const fshLower = firstStructuralHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n   460→    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n   461→      if (s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text) return true;\n   462→      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n   463→      // Remove s if it is a space-delimited prefix of the structural heading\n   464→      return !fshLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \");\n   465→    });\n   466→  }\n   467→\n   468→  // Protect continuation joins: when a multi-line join (2-line or 3-line) survived the threshold\n   469→  // and its second part starts with a continuation character, remove the single-line prefix/suffix\n   470→  // so the dedup \"shorter wins\" rule doesn't destroy the complete join.\n   471→  // Note: the pre-merge step above already handles the common Baked Eggs case (&/continuation\n   472→  // on next line) by turning it into a single candidate — this block covers the rarer case where\n   473→  // a continuation-character join was generated as a 2-line/3-line candidate and the prefix\n   474→  // single also survived threshold independently (e.g. from a different code path or OCR layout).\n   475→  // Safety: only fires for joins whose continuation starts with /&+:( — digit continuations\n   476→  // like \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki\" are NOT protected, so dedup correctly keeps the shorter form.\n   477→  const survivingJoins = selected.filter((s) => s.origin === \"2-line\" || s.origin === \"3-line\");\n   478→  if (survivingJoins.length > 0) {\n   479→    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n   480→      if (s.origin !== \"single\") return true;\n   481→      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n   482→      // Remove PREFIX singles whose continuation join also survived\n   483→      const isPrefixOfJoin = survivingJoins.some((j) => {\n   484→        const jLower = j.text.toLowerCase();\n   485→        if (!jLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \")) return false;\n   486→        const remainder = jLower.slice(sLower.length + 1);\n   487→        return /^[/&+:(]/.test(remainder);\n   488→      });\n   489→      if (isPrefixOfJoin) return false;\n   490→      // Remove SUFFIX singles (e.g. \"& Coriander\") whose parent join also survived\n   491→      const isSuffixOfJoin = survivingJoins.some((j) => {\n   492→        const jLower = j.text.toLowerCase();\n   493→        if (!jLower.endsWith(\" \" + sLower)) return false;\n   494→        // Only remove if the suffix starts with a continuation character\n   495→        return /^[/&+:(]/.test(sLower);\n   496→      });\n   497→      if (isSuffixOfJoin) return false;\n   498→      return true;\n   499→    });\n   500→  }\n   501→\n   502→  // Pre-dedup: remove sub-section headers that are substrings of other surviving candidates.\n   503→  // A sub-section header is an ALL_CAPS candidate followed by ingredient-like lines in the source.\n   504→  // Example: \"CHLEBEK\" (bread section header, followed by \"500 g mąki\") is a substring of\n   505→  // \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\" (the real title). Without this filter, dedup kills the title.\n   506→  selected = selected.filter((candidate) => {\n   507→    if (!isAllCaps(candidate.text)) return true;\n   508→    // Check if this candidate is immediately followed by ingredient-like content\n   509→    const nextSourceLines = lines.slice(candidate.position + 1, candidate.position + 2);\n   510→    const followedByIngredients = nextSourceLines.some(\n   511→      (l) => looksLikeIngredient(l.trim()) || startsWithNumber(l.trim())\n   512→    );\n   513→    if (!followedByIngredients) return true;\n   514→    // Only remove if a longer candidate contains this one as a substring\n   515→    const candidateLower = candidate.text.toLowerCase();\n   516→    const hasLongerParent = selected.some(\n   517→      (other) =>\n   518→        other !== candidate &&\n   519→        other.text.length > candidate.text.length &&\n   520→        other.text.toLowerCase().includes(candidateLower)\n   521→    );\n   522→    return !hasLongerParent;\n   523→  });\n   524→\n   525→  // Deduplicate: if one title is a substring of another, keep the shorter (more focused) one.\n   526→  // DO NOT CHANGE THIS LOGIC — it has been incorrectly \"improved\" by the title-loop 5 times.\n   527→  // The tests require shorter wins: \"Pierogi Ruskie\" over \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki 3 ziemniaki\".\n   528→  // The pre-filter above handles the conflicting case (structural heading prefix removal) so that\n   529→  // the incomplete prefix line is never present here when the complete join is in selected.\n   530→  selected = selected.filter((a) => {\n   531→    const aLower = a.text.toLowerCase();\n   532→    return !selected.some(\n   533→      (b) =>\n   534→        b !== a &&\n   535→        aLower.includes(b.text.toLowerCase()) &&\n   536→        b.text.length < a.text.length\n   537→    );\n   538→  });\n   539→\n   540→  // Multi-title guard: only join multiple candidates with \"+\" when there is\n   541→  // structural evidence of a multi-recipe page (≥2 ALL_CAPS headings).\n   542→  // A single ALL_CAPS title among mixed-case survivors is a single-recipe page —\n   543→  // collapse to the highest-scoring candidate.\n   544→  // Zero ALL_CAPS survivors → mixed-case multi-title page → keep all.\n   545→  if (selected.length > 1) {\n   546→    const allCapsSelected = selected.filter((s) => isAllCaps(s.text));\n   547→    if (allCapsSelected.length >= 2) {\n   548→      // Check whether non-first ALL_CAPS headings are section headers within one recipe\n   549→      // (followed immediately by ingredient-like content) rather than separate recipe titles.\n   550→      // A multi-recipe page has body text between titles; a single-recipe page has\n   551→      // ingredient lines immediately after each section heading.\n   552→      const sortedCaps = [...allCapsSelected].sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position);\n   553→      const isSubHeader = sortedCaps.slice(1).every((cap) => {\n   554→        const nextLines = lines.slice(cap.position + 1, cap.position + 3);\n   555→        return nextLines.some(\n   556→          (l) => looksLikeIngredient(l.trim()) || /^\\s*\\d/.test(l.trim())\n   557→        );\n   558→      });\n   559→      if (isSubHeader) {\n   560→        selected = [sortedCaps[0]];\n   561→      } else {\n   562→        selected = allCapsSelected;\n   563→      }\n   564→    } else if (allCapsSelected.length === 1) {\n   565→      selected = [selected.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n   566→    }\n   567→  }\n   568→\n   569→  // Cap at 3, sort by document position\n   570→  selected.sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position);\n   571→  selected = selected.slice(0, 3);\n   572→\n   573→  if (selected.length === 0) {\n   574→    return undefined;\n   575→  }\n   576→\n   577→  return selected.map((s) => s.text).join(\" + \");\n   578→}\n   579→\n   580→/**\n   581→ * Extract potential recipe title from OCR text (sync heuristic fallback)\n   582→ */\n   583→export function extractTitle(text: string): string | undefined {\n   584→  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) {\n   585→    return undefined;\n   586→  }\n   587→\n   588→  const lines = text.split(\"\\n\").map((line) => line.trim());\n   589→\n   590→  for (const line of lines) {\n   591→    if (line.length === 0) continue;\n   592→    if (line.length < 3 || line.length > 50) continue;\n   593→    if (looksLikeIngredient(line)) continue;\n   594→    if (isAllCaps(line)) continue;\n   595→    if (startsWithNumber(line)) continue;\n   596→    return line;\n   597→  }\n   598→\n   599→  return undefined;\n   600→}\n   601→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e5c8568-eb2f-4e0e-8771-787e6907f7e7","uuid":"b769bd7d-ba1f-4263-a366-32ebdf042738","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/lib/text-classifier/title-extractor.ts","content":"/**\n * Title Extraction\n * Extracts potential recipe title from OCR text using heuristics or semantic embeddings\n */\n\nimport { cosineSimilarity } from \"./embeddings\";\n\nexport type EmbedFn = (text: string) => Promise<Array<number>>;\n\nconst TITLE_REFERENCE =\n  \"recipe name, dish title, name of the food, nazwa przepisu, nazwa dania\";\nconst HEADER_REFERENCE =\n  \"ingredients list, cooking directions, section heading, składniki, przygotowanie, sposób wykonania\";\nconst NOISE_REFERENCE =\n  \"page number, table of contents, book footer, garbled text\";\n\n/**\n * Measurement units commonly found in ingredient lists\n */\nconst MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS = [\n  \"cup\",\n  \"cups\",\n  \"tbsp\",\n  \"tsp\",\n  \"tablespoon\",\n  \"teaspoon\",\n  \"oz\",\n  \"lb\",\n  \"gram\",\n  \"grams\",\n  \"kg\",\n  \"ml\",\n  \"liter\",\n  \"pinch\",\n  \"dash\",\n  \"handful\",\n];\n\n/**\n * Patterns that identify recipe metadata lines (not titles)\n */\nconst METADATA_PATTERNS = [\n  /^(SERVES?|MAKES?|YIELDS?)\\b/i,\n  /^(PREP(ARATION)?|COOK(ING)?|PROOF|RISING|FERMENTATION|REST(ING)?)\\s*(AND\\s*)?(COOK(ING)?)?\\s*TIME/i,\n  /^SAMPLE\\s+SCHEDULE\\b/i,\n  /^BULK\\s+FERMENTATION\\b/i,\n  /^(THIS\\s+RECIPE\\s+)?MAKES\\b/i,\n  // Polish serving-size patterns: \"NA 3 PAPRYKI\", \"NA OKOŁO 1 KG\", \"DLA 4 OSÓB\"\n  /^NA\\s+(\\d|OKOŁO)\\b/i,\n  /^DLA\\s+\\d/i,\n  // Time-unit metadata: any line containing \"N MIN\" or \"N GODZ\" is prep/cook/rest time,\n  // regardless of OCR-corrupted prefix (catches PRZYGOTOWANTE, GOTOMANTE, etc.)\n  /\\b\\d+\\s*MIN\\b/i,\n  /\\b\\d+\\s*GODZ/i,\n];\n\n/**\n * Single-word non-title words — standalone OCR fragments unlikely to be recipe titles\n */\nconst NON_TITLE_WORDS = new Set([\n  \"the\", \"and\", \"for\", \"but\", \"not\", \"you\", \"all\", \"can\", \"are\", \"was\",\n  \"has\", \"his\", \"her\", \"its\", \"our\", \"who\", \"how\", \"may\", \"new\", \"now\",\n  \"old\", \"see\", \"way\", \"did\", \"get\", \"let\", \"say\", \"she\", \"too\", \"use\",\n  \"buns\", \"with\",\n]);\n\nfunction looksLikeIngredient(line: string): boolean {\n  const lowerLine = line.toLowerCase();\n  return MEASUREMENT_PATTERNS.some((pattern) => lowerLine.includes(pattern));\n}\n\nfunction startsWithNumber(line: string): boolean {\n  return /^\\s*\\d/.test(line);\n}\n\nfunction isAllCaps(line: string): boolean {\n  const letters = line.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\");\n  return letters.length > 0 && letters === letters.toUpperCase();\n}\n\nfunction looksLikeMetadata(text: string): boolean {\n  return METADATA_PATTERNS.some((pattern) => pattern.test(text.trim()));\n}\n\nfunction isLikelyGarbled(text: string): boolean {\n  const letters = text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\");\n  if (letters.length < 2) return true;\n\n  // Check vowel ratio — English/Polish text typically has 30–50% vowels\n  const vowels = letters.replace(/[^aeiouAEIOUyYąęóĄĘÓ]/g, \"\").length;\n  const vowelRatio = vowels / letters.length;\n  if (vowelRatio < 0.15 || vowelRatio > 0.85) return true;\n\n  // Single orphaned word ≤3 letters that isn't a common word\n  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n  const COMMON_SHORT = new Set([\n    \"the\", \"and\", \"for\", \"but\", \"not\", \"you\", \"all\", \"can\", \"had\", \"her\",\n    \"was\", \"one\", \"our\", \"out\", \"are\", \"has\", \"his\", \"how\", \"its\", \"may\",\n    \"new\", \"now\", \"old\", \"see\", \"way\", \"who\", \"did\", \"get\", \"let\", \"say\",\n    \"she\", \"too\", \"use\",\n  ]);\n  if (words.length === 1 && letters.length <= 3 && !COMMON_SHORT.has(text.trim().toLowerCase())) {\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Recipe titles never start with a lowercase letter\n  if (/^[a-z]/.test(text.trim())) {\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Mid-text sentence boundary (\". \" followed by a letter) — body text fragment spliced from multiple sentences\n  const trimmed = text.trim();\n  if (/\\.\\s+[a-zA-Z]/.test(trimmed) && !trimmed.endsWith(\")\")) {\n    return true;\n  }\n\n  // Multi-word candidate containing a garbled OCR fragment: a short lowercase word that isn't a known short word\n  if (words.length >= 2) {\n    const commonShort2 = new Set([\n      \"a\", \"i\", \"of\", \"or\", \"to\", \"in\", \"on\", \"is\", \"it\", \"an\",\n      \"as\", \"at\", \"by\", \"do\", \"go\", \"if\", \"no\", \"so\", \"up\", \"we\",\n      \"w\", \"z\",  // Polish prepositions\n    ]);\n    const hasGarbledWord = words.some(\n      (w) =>\n        /^[a-z]/.test(w) &&\n        w.replace(/[^a-z]/g, \"\").length <= 2 &&\n        !commonShort2.has(w.toLowerCase())\n    );\n    if (hasGarbledWord) {\n      return true;\n    }\n  }\n\n  return false;\n}\n\nfunction passesHardFilters(text: string): boolean {\n  if (text.length < 3 || text.length > 80) return false;\n  if (looksLikeIngredient(text)) return false;\n  if (startsWithNumber(text)) return false;\n  if (looksLikeMetadata(text)) return false;\n  if (isLikelyGarbled(text)) return false;\n  // Single-word non-title fragments\n  const words = text.trim().split(/\\s+/);\n  if (words.length === 1 && NON_TITLE_WORDS.has(text.trim().toLowerCase())) return false;\n  return true;\n}\n\n/**\n * Detect initial burst of short garbled lines.\n * Returns the index of the first non-garbled or long line.\n */\nfunction findBurstEnd(lines: Array<{ text: string }>): number {\n  let i = 0;\n  while (i < lines.length && lines[i].text.length < 20 && isLikelyGarbled(lines[i].text)) {\n    i++;\n  }\n  return i;\n}\n\nfunction wordCount(text: string): number {\n  return text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.length > 0).length;\n}\n\n/**\n * Build candidate strings from lines: single lines plus multi-line joins (2-3 consecutive).\n * Skips initial burst of short garbled lines. Scans all remaining lines. Caps at 25.\n */\nexport type CandidateOrigin = \"single\" | \"2-line\" | \"3-line\";\n\nfunction buildCandidates(\n  lines: Array<string>\n): Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }> {\n  const nonEmptyLines: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n\n  for (let i = 0; i < lines.length; i++) {\n    const trimmed = lines[i].trim();\n    if (trimmed.length > 0) {\n      nonEmptyLines.push({ text: trimmed, index: i });\n    }\n  }\n\n  const burstEnd = findBurstEnd(nonEmptyLines);\n\n  // Pre-merge continuation lines: a line starting with /&+:( is never a standalone title.\n  // Merge it into the preceding line so the complete title enters the pool as a single candidate,\n  // avoiding the fragile chain of conditions required by the downstream join survival logic.\n  // Limitation: only one continuation line per preceding line is merged. Titles split across\n  // three or more lines with continuation tokens (rare in practice) are not handled here —\n  // the downstream 2-line and 3-line join candidates cover those cases instead.\n  const mergedLines: Array<{ text: string; index: number }> = [];\n  for (let i = burstEnd; i < nonEmptyLines.length; i++) {\n    const line = nonEmptyLines[i];\n    if (i + 1 < nonEmptyLines.length) {\n      const nextText = nonEmptyLines[i + 1].text;\n      if (/^[/&+:(]/.test(nextText)) {\n        mergedLines.push({ text: `${line.text} ${nextText}`, index: line.index });\n        i++;\n        continue;\n      }\n    }\n    mergedLines.push(line);\n  }\n\n  const candidates: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin }> = [];\n  const seen = new Set<string>();\n\n  for (let i = 0; i < mergedLines.length; i++) {\n    const line = mergedLines[i];\n\n    // Single line\n    if (passesHardFilters(line.text)) {\n      const norm = line.text.toLowerCase();\n      if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n        seen.add(norm);\n        candidates.push({ text: line.text, position: line.index, origin: \"single\" });\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 2-line join\n    if (i + 1 < mergedLines.length) {\n      const joined2 = `${line.text} ${mergedLines[i + 1].text}`;\n      if (passesHardFilters(joined2)) {\n        const norm = joined2.toLowerCase();\n        if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n          seen.add(norm);\n          candidates.push({ text: joined2, position: line.index, origin: \"2-line\" });\n        }\n      }\n    }\n\n    // 3-line join\n    if (i + 2 < mergedLines.length) {\n      const joined3 = `${line.text} ${mergedLines[i + 1].text} ${mergedLines[i + 2].text}`;\n      if (passesHardFilters(joined3)) {\n        const norm = joined3.toLowerCase();\n        if (!seen.has(norm)) {\n          seen.add(norm);\n          candidates.push({ text: joined3, position: line.index, origin: \"3-line\" });\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Pre-filter to 25 before embedding calls: prefer ALL_CAPS and short candidates.\n  // Position-based scoring handles final ranking.\n  if (candidates.length > 25) {\n    const prioritized = candidates.slice().sort((a, b) => {\n      const aAllCaps = isAllCaps(a.text) ? 0 : 1;\n      const bAllCaps = isAllCaps(b.text) ? 0 : 1;\n      if (aAllCaps !== bAllCaps) return aAllCaps - bAllCaps;\n      const aShort = wordCount(a.text) <= 5 ? 0 : 1;\n      const bShort = wordCount(b.text) <= 5 ? 0 : 1;\n      return aShort - bShort;\n    });\n    return prioritized.slice(0, 25);\n  }\n\n  return candidates;\n}\n\n// Module-level cache for reference embeddings\nlet cachedTitleRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\nlet cachedHeaderRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\nlet cachedNoiseRefEmbedding: Array<number> | null = null;\n\nexport function _resetEmbeddingCacheForTests(): void {\n  cachedTitleRefEmbedding = null;\n  cachedHeaderRefEmbedding = null;\n  cachedNoiseRefEmbedding = null;\n}\n\nexport async function extractTitleWithEmbeddings(\n  text: string,\n  embed: EmbedFn\n): Promise<string | undefined> {\n  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  const lines = text.split(\"\\n\");\n  const candidates = buildCandidates(lines);\n\n  if (candidates.length === 0) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  // Cache reference embeddings\n  if (!cachedTitleRefEmbedding) {\n    cachedTitleRefEmbedding = await embed(TITLE_REFERENCE);\n  }\n  if (!cachedHeaderRefEmbedding) {\n    cachedHeaderRefEmbedding = await embed(HEADER_REFERENCE);\n  }\n  if (!cachedNoiseRefEmbedding) {\n    cachedNoiseRefEmbedding = await embed(NOISE_REFERENCE);\n  }\n\n  // Find ALL_CAPS candidates with ≥2 words where every significant word has ≥4 alpha letters.\n  // Insignificant tokens (≤1 alpha letter: \"/\", \"&\", \"+\", \":\", \"D)\", etc.) are filtered before\n  // the check so that multi-line joins with continuation punctuation still qualify.\n  const isStructuralHeading = (c: { text: string }): boolean => {\n    if (!isAllCaps(c.text) || wordCount(c.text) < 2) return false;\n    const sigWords = c.text.trim().split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length > 1);\n    return sigWords.length >= 2 && sigWords.every((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n  };\n\n  // Pass 1: compute rawScore for all candidates (embedding quality signal)\n  const rawScored: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin; rawScore: number; embedding: Array<number> }> = [];\n  for (const candidate of candidates) {\n    const embedding = await embed(candidate.text);\n    const titleSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedTitleRefEmbedding);\n    const headerSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedHeaderRefEmbedding);\n    const noiseSim = cosineSimilarity(embedding, cachedNoiseRefEmbedding);\n    const rawScore = titleSim - Math.max(headerSim, noiseSim);\n    rawScored.push({ text: candidate.text, position: candidate.position, origin: candidate.origin, rawScore, embedding });\n  }\n\n  // Select baseHeading by embedding quality (rawScore), not position.\n  // This prevents OCR-garbled fragments from claiming the structural heading slot.\n  const structuralCandidates = rawScored.filter((s) => isStructuralHeading(s));\n\n  // Penalize structural headings with truncated OCR words:\n  // if \"FRON\" appears and another heading has \"SAFFRON\", \"FRON\" is likely garbled.\n  for (const sc of structuralCandidates) {\n    const sigWords = sc.text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n    for (const other of structuralCandidates) {\n      if (other === sc) continue;\n      const otherSigWords = other.text.split(/\\s+/).filter((w) => w.replace(/[^A-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4);\n      const hasTruncation = sigWords.some((w) =>\n        otherSigWords.some((ow) => ow !== w && ow.length > w.length && ow.endsWith(w))\n      );\n      if (hasTruncation) {\n        sc.rawScore = -1.0;  // Hard disqualification — truncated OCR artifact\n        break;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  const bestStructural = structuralCandidates.length > 0\n    ? structuralCandidates.reduce((a, b) => {\n        const scoreDiff = a.rawScore - b.rawScore;\n        if (Math.abs(scoreDiff) > 0.03) return scoreDiff > 0 ? a : b;\n        // Tiebreak: single-line origin beats multi-line joins (avoids conflating two separate headings)\n        if (a.origin === \"single\" && b.origin !== \"single\") return a;\n        if (b.origin === \"single\" && a.origin !== \"single\") return b;\n        // Tiebreak: more words (more specific) → better\n        const wcDiff = wordCount(b.text) - wordCount(a.text);\n        if (wcDiff !== 0) return wcDiff > 0 ? b : a;\n        // Tiebreak: earlier position → better\n        return a.position < b.position ? a : b;\n      })\n    : null;\n  const baseHeading = bestStructural ?? undefined;\n\n  // When the best structural heading has a continuation on the next line introduced by a\n  // punctuation token (/, &, +, :, or parenthesis), prefer the longer 2-line join as the\n  // complete heading. E.g. \"SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK\" + \"/ COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)\".\n  // Guard: the remainder after the prefix must start with a continuation character to avoid\n  // merging two separate consecutive recipe titles (FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS stays separate\n  // from FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS because \"FINNISH\" does not start with a continuation token).\n  const firstStructuralHeading = baseHeading && (\n    rawScored.find((c) => {\n      if (!isStructuralHeading(c)) return false;\n      const hLower = baseHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n      const cLower = c.text.toLowerCase();\n      return cLower.startsWith(hLower + \" \") && /^[/&+:(]/.test(cLower.slice(hLower.length + 1));\n    }) ?? baseHeading\n  );\n\n  // Pass 2: apply bonuses\n  const scored: Array<{ text: string; position: number; origin: CandidateOrigin; score: number; rawScore: number; baseScore: number; thresholdScore: number }> = rawScored.map((rs) => {\n    // Position factor: multiplicative tiebreaker — amplifies existing signal, doesn't replace it\n    const relativePosition = rs.position / lines.length;\n    const positionFactor = relativePosition < 0.5\n      ? 1.0 + 0.12 * (1 - relativePosition * 2)\n      : 1.0;\n\n    // ALL_CAPS bonus: recipe books use ALL_CAPS for titles and section headings\n    const allCapsBonus = isAllCaps(rs.text) && rs.text.replace(/[^a-zA-Z]/g, \"\").length >= 4\n      ? 0.08\n      : 0;\n\n    // Structural heading bonus: best ALL_CAPS heading (or its continuation join) is almost always the recipe title\n    const structuralBonus = firstStructuralHeading && rs.text === firstStructuralHeading.text ? 0.10 : 0;\n\n    // thresholdScore excludes structural bonus so the bonus doesn't inflate the threshold\n    // and prevent equally-valid structural headings from passing on multi-recipe pages.\n    const thresholdScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus;\n    // baseScore excludes position factor — used for diagnostics and ranking\n    const baseScore = rs.rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n    const score = rs.rawScore * positionFactor + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus;\n    return { text: rs.text, position: rs.position, origin: rs.origin, score, rawScore: rs.rawScore, baseScore, thresholdScore };\n  });\n\n  if (scored.length === 0) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  // --- Pre-threshold bilingual title detection ---\n  // When a mixed-case candidate at position 0 is followed by an ALL_CAPS candidate\n  // at position ≤ 2 that is semantically similar to it, this is a bilingual recipe\n  // page (e.g., Polish title + ALL_CAPS Korean romanization). Suppress confirmed\n  // translation candidates before computing threshold so their bonuses don't inflate\n  // the threshold beyond the mixed-case title's reach.\n  // Note: we check position ≤ 2 (local proximity), not global ALL_CAPS count, so\n  // section headers later in the document (SKŁADNIKI, WARZYWA, etc.) are irrelevant.\n  let scoredForThreshold = scored;\n  const prePos0 = scored.find((s) => s.position === 0 && !isAllCaps(s.text));\n  if (prePos0) {\n    const nearbyAllCaps = scored.filter(\n      (s) => isAllCaps(s.text) && s.position >= 1 && s.position <= 2\n    );\n    const pos0Embedding = rawScored.find((r) => r.text === prePos0.text)?.embedding;\n    if (pos0Embedding && nearbyAllCaps.length > 0) {\n      const translationCandidates = nearbyAllCaps.filter((cap) => {\n        const capEmbedding = rawScored.find((r) => r.text === cap.text)?.embedding;\n        if (!capEmbedding) return false;\n        return cosineSimilarity(pos0Embedding, capEmbedding) > 0.4;\n      });\n      if (translationCandidates.length > 0) {\n        // Also suppress multi-line joins that start with the translation text\n        // (e.g. \"PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM Ingredients\" starts with \"PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM\")\n        scoredForThreshold = scored.filter((s) => {\n          const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n          return !translationCandidates.some((t) => sLower.startsWith(t.text.toLowerCase()));\n        });\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Use thresholdScore (excludes structural bonus) so the structural bonus doesn't inflate\n  // the threshold and block equally-valid headings on multi-recipe pages.\n  const bestThresholdScore = Math.max(...scoredForThreshold.map((s) => s.thresholdScore));\n  const threshold = Math.max(0.08, bestThresholdScore * 0.7);\n\n  // Filter candidates above threshold\n  let selected = scoredForThreshold.filter((s) => s.score >= threshold);\n\n  // Empty-pool fallback: when threshold filtering discards every candidate,\n  // the hard filters' structural verdict should not be overruled by weak\n  // embedding differentiation. Return the best positional candidate.\n  if (selected.length === 0 && scored.length > 0) {\n    const fallback = scored\n      .slice()\n      .sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position || b.score - a.score);\n    selected = [fallback[0]];\n  }\n\n  // Remove word-boundary prefixes of firstStructuralHeading when the heading itself survived\n  // the threshold. Cases:\n  //   ARAYES case:  firstStructuralHeading = \"ARAYES SHRAK\" (2-word join qualifies; \"ARAYES\"\n  //     alone = 1 word, so it never qualified). Filter removes \"ARAYES\" so dedup keeps the join.\n  //   SAFFRON case: baseHeading was the partial line; continuation logic above upgraded\n  //     firstStructuralHeading to the full join. Filter removes the partial so dedup keeps join.\n  // Safety: only fires when the complete heading itself is in selected (passed the threshold).\n  if (firstStructuralHeading && selected.some((s) => s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text)) {\n    const fshLower = firstStructuralHeading.text.toLowerCase();\n    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n      if (s.text === firstStructuralHeading.text) return true;\n      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n      // Remove s if it is a space-delimited prefix of the structural heading\n      return !fshLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \");\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Protect continuation joins: when a multi-line join (2-line or 3-line) survived the threshold\n  // and its second part starts with a continuation character, remove the single-line prefix/suffix\n  // so the dedup \"shorter wins\" rule doesn't destroy the complete join.\n  // Note: the pre-merge step above already handles the common Baked Eggs case (&/continuation\n  // on next line) by turning it into a single candidate — this block covers the rarer case where\n  // a continuation-character join was generated as a 2-line/3-line candidate and the prefix\n  // single also survived threshold independently (e.g. from a different code path or OCR layout).\n  // Safety: only fires for joins whose continuation starts with /&+:( — digit continuations\n  // like \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki\" are NOT protected, so dedup correctly keeps the shorter form.\n  const survivingJoins = selected.filter((s) => s.origin === \"2-line\" || s.origin === \"3-line\");\n  if (survivingJoins.length > 0) {\n    selected = selected.filter((s) => {\n      if (s.origin !== \"single\") return true;\n      const sLower = s.text.toLowerCase();\n      // Remove PREFIX singles whose continuation join also survived\n      const isPrefixOfJoin = survivingJoins.some((j) => {\n        const jLower = j.text.toLowerCase();\n        if (!jLower.startsWith(sLower + \" \")) return false;\n        const remainder = jLower.slice(sLower.length + 1);\n        return /^[/&+:(]/.test(remainder);\n      });\n      if (isPrefixOfJoin) return false;\n      // Remove SUFFIX singles (e.g. \"& Coriander\") whose parent join also survived\n      const isSuffixOfJoin = survivingJoins.some((j) => {\n        const jLower = j.text.toLowerCase();\n        if (!jLower.endsWith(\" \" + sLower)) return false;\n        // Only remove if the suffix starts with a continuation character\n        return /^[/&+:(]/.test(sLower);\n      });\n      if (isSuffixOfJoin) return false;\n      return true;\n    });\n  }\n\n  // Pre-dedup: remove sub-section headers that are substrings of other surviving candidates.\n  // A sub-section header is an ALL_CAPS candidate followed by ingredient-like lines in the source.\n  // Example: \"CHLEBEK\" (bread section header, followed by \"500 g mąki\") is a substring of\n  // \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\" (the real title). Without this filter, dedup kills the title.\n  selected = selected.filter((candidate) => {\n    if (!isAllCaps(candidate.text)) return true;\n    // Check if this candidate is immediately followed by ingredient-like content\n    const nextSourceLines = lines.slice(candidate.position + 1, candidate.position + 2);\n    const followedByIngredients = nextSourceLines.some(\n      (l) => looksLikeIngredient(l.trim()) || startsWithNumber(l.trim())\n    );\n    if (!followedByIngredients) return true;\n    // Only remove if a longer candidate contains this one as a substring\n    const candidateLower = candidate.text.toLowerCase();\n    const hasLongerParent = selected.some(\n      (other) =>\n        other !== candidate &&\n        other.text.length > candidate.text.length &&\n        other.text.toLowerCase().includes(candidateLower)\n    );\n    return !hasLongerParent;\n  });\n\n  // Deduplicate: if one title is a substring of another, keep the shorter (more focused) one.\n  // DO NOT CHANGE THIS LOGIC — it has been incorrectly \"improved\" by the title-loop 5 times.\n  // The tests require shorter wins: \"Pierogi Ruskie\" over \"Pierogi Ruskie 200g mąki 3 ziemniaki\".\n  // The pre-filter above handles the conflicting case (structural heading prefix removal) so that\n  // the incomplete prefix line is never present here when the complete join is in selected.\n  selected = selected.filter((a) => {\n    const aLower = a.text.toLowerCase();\n    return !selected.some(\n      (b) =>\n        b !== a &&\n        aLower.includes(b.text.toLowerCase()) &&\n        b.text.length < a.text.length\n    );\n  });\n\n  // Multi-title guard: only join multiple candidates with \"+\" when there is\n  // structural evidence of a multi-recipe page (≥2 ALL_CAPS headings).\n  // A single ALL_CAPS title among mixed-case survivors is a single-recipe page —\n  // collapse to the highest-scoring candidate.\n  // Zero ALL_CAPS survivors → mixed-case multi-title page → keep all.\n  if (selected.length > 1) {\n    const allCapsSelected = selected.filter((s) => isAllCaps(s.text));\n    if (allCapsSelected.length >= 2) {\n      // Check whether non-first ALL_CAPS headings are section headers within one recipe\n      // (followed immediately by ingredient-like content) rather than separate recipe titles.\n      // A multi-recipe page has body text between titles; a single-recipe page has\n      // ingredient lines immediately after each section heading.\n      const sortedCaps = [...allCapsSelected].sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position);\n      const isSubHeader = sortedCaps.slice(1).every((cap) => {\n        const nextLines = lines.slice(cap.position + 1, cap.position + 3);\n        return nextLines.some(\n          (l) => looksLikeIngredient(l.trim()) || /^\\s*\\d/.test(l.trim())\n        );\n      });\n      if (isSubHeader) {\n        selected = [sortedCaps[0]];\n      } else {\n        selected = allCapsSelected;\n      }\n    } else if (allCapsSelected.length === 1) {\n      selected = [selected.reduce((a, b) => (a.score > b.score ? a : b))];\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Cap at 3, sort by document position\n  selected.sort((a, b) => a.position - b.position);\n  selected = selected.slice(0, 3);\n\n  if (selected.length === 0) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  return selected.map((s) => s.text).join(\" + \");\n}\n\n/**\n * Extract potential recipe title from OCR text (sync heuristic fallback)\n */\nexport function extractTitle(text: string): string | undefined {\n  if (!text || text.trim().length === 0) {\n    return undefined;\n  }\n\n  const lines = text.split(\"\\n\").map((line) => line.trim());\n\n  for (const line of lines) {\n    if (line.length === 0) continue;\n    if (line.length < 3 || line.length > 50) continue;\n    if (looksLikeIngredient(line)) continue;\n    if (isAllCaps(line)) continue;\n    if (startsWithNumber(line)) continue;\n    return line;\n  }\n\n  return undefined;\n}\n","numLines":601,"startLine":1,"totalLines":601}}}
