{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0144PXmjEmy913inJ4U8ScKn","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive picture. Let me compile the summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Summary of Title Extraction Iteration History (1-11)\n\n### Overview\nThe title extraction algorithm has gone through 11 iterations, progressing from **16.7% accuracy (1/6 cases)** to **87.5% accuracy (7/8 cases)**. The most recent iteration (11) introduced a regression where only 1 of 8 test cases fails.\n\n### Current State (Iteration 11)\n- **Passing**: 7/8 test cases (87.5%)\n- **Failing**: 1 test case\n  - CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM → returns `CHLEBEK` instead of the full title\n\n---\n\n## Iteration-by-Iteration Breakdown\n\n### Iterations 1-3: Foundational Issues (16.7% → 33.3% accuracy)\n\n**Key Failures Pattern (Iteration 1):**\n- ARAYES SHRAK → extracted partial \"ARAYES\"\n- Baked Eggs with Feta → extracted with spurious metadata \"SERVES\"\n- Finnish Flatbreads → extracted garbled \"DAT FLATBREADS\"\n- Mixed Seed Crispbread → extracted garbage \"sheet in to heat up\"\n- Saffron Wheat Buns → extracted corrupted fragments\n\n**Root Causes Identified:**\n1. **Inverted substring deduplication**: Kept shorter candidates when one was a substring of another (discarded complete titles)\n2. **No metadata filtering**: Lines like \"SERVES\", \"MAKES\", \"PREP TIME\" competed as titles\n3. **No OCR quality gating**: Garbled fragments passed all filters\n4. **Embedding scoring unreliable**: Technique-oriented titles embedded poorly vs. reference phrase\n5. **Position bonus too aggressive**: Outweighed semantic signals entirely\n6. **Multi-line title fragility**: Split titles (2-line joins) lost to partial fragments\n\n**Iteration 2 Fix Attempt:**\n- Fixed dedup logic to prefer longer candidates when one contains another\n- Still had issues with multi-recipe pages\n\n**Iteration 3 Insights:**\n- Substring dedup rule was still problematic for multi-line joins\n- Position factor × threshold interaction excluded second titles on multi-recipe pages\n- Revealed that `rawScore` comparisons in dedup ignored structural bonuses earned by full joins\n\n---\n\n### Iterations 4-6: Structural Filtering & Bonuses (33.3% → 66.7%)\n\n**Major advances** in hard filters and structural heading detection:\n- Added metadata pattern filtering (SERVES, MAKES, YIELDS, etc.)\n- Implemented `isStructuralHeading()` to identify ALL_CAPS headings\n- Introduced ALL_CAPS bonus (+0.08) and structural heading bonus (+0.10)\n- Added position factor based on line position\n- Implemented continuation join protection for lines starting with `&`, `/`, `+`, `:`\n\n**Emerging Pattern:**\nTests passing stably: ARAYES SHRAK, FINNISH FLATBREADS, MIXED SEED CRISPBREAD, OVERNIGHT PIZZA DOUGH, PIEROGI RUSKIE (implied from later tests)\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 7: Failure Analysis on Remaining Cases (50% baseline)\n\n**Failures identified:**\n1. **Baked Eggs with Feta** → truncated (missing \"& Coriander\")\n   - Root cause: Continuation join scored below embedding threshold despite passing hard filters\n   - Embedding model penalizes ingredient-bearing titles (Feta, Harissa → similar to ingredient lists)\n   \n2. **CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM** → returned both the title AND sub-section header joined with \"+\"\n   - Root cause: Algorithm cannot distinguish sub-section headers from second recipe titles\n   - Multi-title guard fired on 2 ALL_CAPS candidates without checking if they're in same recipe\n   \n3. **Faszerowana papryka** → returned \"PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM\" (Korean romanization)\n   - Root cause: ALL_CAPS bonuses (+0.18 combined) override first-line mixed-case title\n   - Polish title had lower embedding similarity to English TITLE_REFERENCE\n   \n4. **SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS** → truncated/mismatched\n   - Issue A: OCR reads \"/\" but expected title has \":\" (evaluation harness issue)\n   - Issue B: 25-candidate pre-filter cuts the long 9-word join, keeping only partial 5-word version\n\n**Key Insights:**\n- Continuation joins are fragile (depend on long chain of conditions)\n- ALL_CAPS bias defeats mixed-case titles in bilingual recipes\n- Evaluation harness has separator normalization issues\n- Ground truth expectations can be impossible to match when OCR misreads characters\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 8: Implementing Structural Pre-Processing (75% → ?)\n\n**Planned fixes from Iteration 7:**\n1. **Pre-merge continuation lines** (before candidate generation) → direct fix for split titles\n2. **Ingredient-gap detection** in multi-title guard → distinguish section headers from second titles\n3. **First-line mixed-case protection** → prefer bilingual primary titles over romanizations\n4. **Eval harness fix** → normalize separators\n\n**Iteration 8 Results:**\n- 75% passing (6/8)\n- New failures introduced:\n\n**Failures in Iteration 8:**\n1. **Baked Eggs** → empty string `''`\n   - Pre-merge worked correctly, but embedding scorer rated ingredient-bearing title below threshold\n   - No fallback for unambiguous sole candidate\n   - \"Harissa Tomato Sauce\", \"Feta\", \"Coriander\" pulled embedding toward HEADER_REFERENCE\n   \n2. **Faszerowana papryka** → still \"PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM\"\n   - First-line protection condition too strict: requires candidate to survive threshold independently\n   - When ALL_CAPS bonuses inflate threshold, mixed-case title cannot reach it\n   - Protection never fires because precondition (both in `selected`) is violated\n\n**Key Realization:**\n- First-line protection is self-defeating: only works when mixed-case title doesn't need it\n- Empty candidate pool needs fallback to best positional candidate\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 9: Pre-Threshold Detection & Fallbacks (87.5% → ?)\n\n**Fixes implemented:**\n1. **Pre-threshold bilingual detection** → suppress ALL_CAPS subtitle before threshold calculation\n   - Moved from post-threshold to pre-threshold\n   - Used semantic similarity check (0.4 threshold) instead of just position + count\n   \n2. **Empty-pool fallback** → when threshold filters everything, return best positional candidate\n   - Safety net for embedding-penalized but structurally-valid titles\n\n**Iteration 9 Results:**\n- 87.5% passing (7/8)\n\n**Remaining Failure:**\n- **Faszerowana papryka** → still \"PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM\"\n\n**Root Cause of Failure:**\n- Bilingual detection condition `preAllCaps.length === 1` too strict\n- Polish recipes have additional ALL_CAPS lines: \"NA 3 PAPRYKI\" (serving size), \"SKŁADNIKI\" (ingredients), \"WARZYWA\" (vegetables)\n- When `preAllCaps.length === 4`, the suppression doesn't fire\n- ALL_CAPS romanization remains in scoring pool and wins via bonuses\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 10: Polish Metadata & Cross-Lingual Robustness (75% → ?)\n\n**Major fixes for Polish recipe patterns:**\n\n**Fix 1: Polish Metadata Patterns**\nAdded to `METADATA_PATTERNS`:\n- Serving sizes: `NA\\s+(\\d|OKOŁO)` (for N items), `DLA\\s+\\d` (for N people)\n- Time units: `\\d+\\s*MIN`, `\\d+\\s*GODZ` (catches OCR corruptions like PRZYGOTOWANTE, GOTOMANTE)\n\n**Fix 2: Pre-dedup Sub-section Header Removal**\n- Before dedup runs, identify and remove ALL_CAPS sub-section headers that are:\n  - Followed by ingredient-like content (strong sub-section signal)\n  - Substrings of longer candidates (conflict resolution)\n\n**Fix 3: Structural Heading Tiebreaker** (optional defense-in-depth)\n- When two structural headings have rawScores within 0.03 of each other:\n  - Prefer longer candidate (more specific = more likely actual title)\n  - If tied on length, prefer earlier position\n\n**Iteration 10 Results:**\n- 75% passing (6/8)\n- Two failures introduced (regressions):\n\n**Failures in Iteration 10:**\n1. **CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM** → returns `CHLEBEK`\n   - Root cause: 25-candidate pre-filter's \"short first\" sorting deprioritizes long titles\n   - \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\" (5 words, status at edge of `wordCount <= 5` boundary)\n   - But actually: structural heading mis-selection + dedup issue\n   \n2. **Faszerowana papryka** → still `PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM`\n   - \"NA 3 PAPRYKI\" survives hard filters (Polish pattern not in filters yet)\n   - Even with bilingual suppression, all-caps bonus on serving size beats mixed-case title\n\n**Correction issued:**\n- CHLEBEK title actually has exactly 5 words (not 6)\n- Real issue: `bestStructural` picks \"WARZYWA I BOCZEK\" instead of full title (cross-lingual embedding noise)\n- Prefix filter targets wrong heading, leaving `CHLEBEK` substring uncaught\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 11: Bilingual Detection Regression (87.5% → 87.5%, but with different failure)\n\n**Single Failure:**\n- **CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM** → returns `CHLEBEK`\n\n**Root Cause: Bilingual Detection False Positive**\n- Book category header \"Lato | Dania główne\" (Summer | Main dishes) at position 0 is mixed-case\n- Bilingual detector mistakes it for a recipe title\n- Compares it to \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\" at position 1\n- Food-domain terms share enough semantic space that similarity exceeds 0.4 threshold\n- Suppression removes the actual recipe title from threshold calculation\n- Downstream prefix removal and pre-dedup filters cannot act because full title missing from `selected`\n- Only \"CHLEBEK\" sub-section header survives\n\n**Key Insights from Iteration 11:**\n1. Book category headers at position 0 break bilingual detection (indistinguishable by position alone)\n2. 0.4 similarity threshold too permissive within food domain\n3. Multiple downstream safety mechanisms are gated on full title being in `selected`\n4. Section headers (WARZYWA, CHLEBEK) resemble recipe titles structurally (short, ALL_CAPS, food words)\n\n---\n\n## Recurring Patterns Across All Iterations\n\n### Pattern 1: Continuation Fragments Breaking Multi-Line Joins\n**Iterations affected**: 1, 2, 3, 7, 8\n- Lines starting with `&`, `/`, `+`, `:` are continuation lines\n- **Iteration 7 fix**: Pre-merge continuation lines before candidate generation\n- **Status after Iteration 8+**: Fixed (no longer failing)\n\n### Pattern 2: ALL_CAPS Bias Against Mixed-Case Bilingual Titles\n**Iterations affected**: 7, 8, 9, 10, 11\n- ALL_CAPS bonuses (+0.08) + structural bonus (+0.10) = +0.18 advantage\n- Overwhelms position factor (×1.12) for mixed-case first-line titles\n- **Iteration 9 fix**: Pre-threshold bilingual detection with semantic similarity validation\n- **Status**: Partially fixed; Iteration 11 shows false-positive edge case\n\n### Pattern 3: Polish Metadata Patterns Not Filtered\n**Iterations affected**: 9, 10, 11\n- Polish serving sizes: \"NA 3 PAPRYKI\", \"DLA 4 OSÓB\"\n- Polish time metadata: \"PRZYGOTOWANIE\", \"GOTOWANIE\", \"OCZEKIWANIE\" + durations\n- **Iteration 10 fix**: Added Polish patterns to `METADATA_PATTERNS`\n- **Status**: Fixed for Faszerowana papryka; CHLEBEK issue persists from other root\n\n### Pattern 4: Sub-Section Headers Defeating Dedup Logic\n**Iterations affected**: 1, 3, 7, 10, 11\n- Bread section \"CHLEBEK\", ingredient section \"WARZYWA I BOCZEK\" treated as candidate titles\n- Dedup rule \"shorter wins\" removes full title when sub-section is its substring\n- **Iteration 10 fix**: Pre-dedup filter removes ALL_CAPS sub-headers followed by ingredients\n- **Status**: Ineffective in Iteration 11 because full title already suppressed upstream\n\n### Pattern 5: Threshold Filtering Overruling Hard Filters\n**Iterations affected**: 1, 7, 8, 9\n- Candidates pass all structural filters but fall below embedding threshold\n- No fallback when sole/best candidate is discarded\n- **Iteration 9 fix**: Empty-pool fallback to best positional candidate when threshold filters all\n- **Status**: Fixed for Baked Eggs; doesn't help when wrong candidate suppressed upstream\n\n### Pattern 6: Cascading Dependency on Full Title Presence\n**Iterations affected**: 10, 11\n- Prefix removal (line 458) gated on `firstStructuralHeading in selected`\n- Pre-dedup filter (line 506) gated on longer parent in `selected`\n- Both fail simultaneously if full title suppressed upstream\n- **Status**: Design fragility; needs upstream fixes to prevent suppression\n\n### Pattern 7: Embedding Model Language Bias\n**Iterations affected**: 1, 7, 8, 9, 10, 11\n- MiniLM is English-centric\n- Polish titles \"Faszerowana papryka\", \"CHLEBEK\" embed poorly vs. English TITLE_REFERENCE\n- Cross-lingual mixing causes structural heading detection to pick wrong candidate\n- **Status**: Partially mitigated by bilingual detection; full solution would need multilingual embedding or language-agnostic scoring\n\n### Pattern 8: Distinguishing Section Headers from Recipe Titles Structurally\n**Iterations affected**: 7, 10, 11\n- Section headers: ALL_CAPS, 1-3 words, followed by ingredients\n- Recipe titles: ALL_CAPS, 3-5+ words, followed by body text\n- Multi-title guard checks for ingredients between titles to distinguish\n- **Status**: Works when both candidates present; fails when one suppressed upstream\n\n---\n\n## Test Input Evolution\n\n### Original Test Set (Iterations 1-6)\n1. **ARAYES SHRAK** — Split ALL_CAPS title across 2 short lines\n2. **Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander** — Mixed-case with ingredient words, split with `&` continuation\n3. **FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS + FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS** — Multi-recipe page with 2 ALL_CAPS titles\n4. **MIXED SEED CRISPBREAD** — ALL_CAPS title buried under OCR garbage\n5. **OVERNIGHT STRAIGHT PIZZA DOUGH** — ALL_CAPS title with technique-oriented semantics\n6. **SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK : COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)** — Long split ALL_CAPS title with special characters\n\n### Extended Test Set (Iterations 7-11)\n7. **Faszerowana papryka** — Polish mixed-case title + ALL_CAPS Korean romanization (bilingual)\n8. (Unreleased in feedback) — Additional test in Iteration 11 suite\n\n### Untracked Inputs in Recent Iterations\n- Kimchi z ogórków\n- MŁODE PORY DUSZONE W PIWIE\n(Mentioned in Iteration 10 improvement plan as benefiting from Polish metadata patterns)\n\n---\n\n## Current Technical Debt & Edge Cases\n\n### Critical Edge Case (Iteration 11)\n- Book category headers at position 0 indistinguishable from recipe titles\n- Bilingual detection fires on category → actual title pair, suppressing real title\n- Requires either:\n  - Stricter position-2-only check (exclude position 0 from bilingual detection)\n  - Higher similarity threshold (e.g., 0.5+ instead of 0.4) to avoid food-domain false positives\n  - Category header recognition (look for `|` separator, metadata structure)\n\n### Fragile Dependency Chain\n1. Full title must survive pre-threshold suppression\n2. Prefix removal depends on it being in `selected`\n3. Pre-dedup filter depends on longer parent in `selected`\n4. Dedup rule depends on both being available for comparison\n5. Multi-title guard fallback only works if something survives\n\n**Fix needed**: Make downstream logic more robust to upstream suppression or add stronger upstream guards\n\n### Polish Language Support\n- Metadata patterns now covered (Iteration 10+)\n- But cross-lingual embedding quality still affects structural heading selection\n- CHLEBEK/WARZYWA conflict stems from `bestStructural` picking wrong heading via rawScore\n\n### Evaluation Harness Debt\n- SAFFRON case: OCR reads \"/\" but expected title has \":\" — impossible to match without separator normalization\n- Noted as out-of-scope for algorithm; resides in `title-loop.py`\n\n---\n\n## Summary Statistics\n\n| Metric | Iteration 1 | Iteration 11 | Notes |\n|--------|-----------|------------|-------|\n| **Accuracy** | 16.7% (1/6) | 87.5% (7/8) | +70.8 percentage points |\n| **Passing Tests** | 1 | 7 | All from original set survive |\n| **Failing Tests** | 5 | 1 | Only CHLEBEK fails |\n| **Root Causes Addressed** | 0 | 7+ | Continuation, metadata, bilingual detection, dedup, etc. |\n| **Known Regressions** | — | 1 | Bilingual detection false positive (Iteration 11) |\n| **Lines of Code (estimated)** | ~200 | ~500+ | Bonuses, filters, guards, fallbacks added |"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a577d31007fe13f2e (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 103632\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 66192</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e5c8568-eb2f-4e0e-8771-787e6907f7e7","uuid":"9a92ea5a-3bbb-48ce-8a9d-b7f682d94e92","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read all the feedback.md and improvement-plan.md files in tools/title-loop/docs/ subdirectories (iterations 1-10). I need to understand:\n1. What failures have occurred across iterations\n2. What fixes were attempted\n3. What patterns keep recurring\n4. What the current test inputs look like\n\nRead at minimum the feedback.md files from iterations 7-10, and any improvement-plan.md files that exist. Also check if there's an iter.txt file in tools/title-loop/docs/ that tracks iteration history.\n\nAlso read tools/title-loop/docs/11-023af39/ to see if there are any other files besides feedback.md.\n\nProvide a comprehensive summary of the iteration history.","agentId":"a577d31007fe13f2e","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive picture. Let me compile the summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Summary of Title Extraction Iteration History (1-11)\n\n### Overview\nThe title extraction algorithm has gone through 11 iterations, progressing from **16.7% accuracy (1/6 cases)** to **87.5% accuracy (7/8 cases)**. The most recent iteration (11) introduced a regression where only 1 of 8 test cases fails.\n\n### Current State (Iteration 11)\n- **Passing**: 7/8 test cases (87.5%)\n- **Failing**: 1 test case\n  - CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM → returns `CHLEBEK` instead of the full title\n\n---\n\n## Iteration-by-Iteration Breakdown\n\n### Iterations 1-3: Foundational Issues (16.7% → 33.3% accuracy)\n\n**Key Failures Pattern (Iteration 1):**\n- ARAYES SHRAK → extracted partial \"ARAYES\"\n- Baked Eggs with Feta → extracted with spurious metadata \"SERVES\"\n- Finnish Flatbreads → extracted garbled \"DAT FLATBREADS\"\n- Mixed Seed Crispbread → extracted garbage \"sheet in to heat up\"\n- Saffron Wheat Buns → extracted corrupted fragments\n\n**Root Causes Identified:**\n1. **Inverted substring deduplication**: Kept shorter candidates when one was a substring of another (discarded complete titles)\n2. **No metadata filtering**: Lines like \"SERVES\", \"MAKES\", \"PREP TIME\" competed as titles\n3. **No OCR quality gating**: Garbled fragments passed all filters\n4. **Embedding scoring unreliable**: Technique-oriented titles embedded poorly vs. reference phrase\n5. **Position bonus too aggressive**: Outweighed semantic signals entirely\n6. **Multi-line title fragility**: Split titles (2-line joins) lost to partial fragments\n\n**Iteration 2 Fix Attempt:**\n- Fixed dedup logic to prefer longer candidates when one contains another\n- Still had issues with multi-recipe pages\n\n**Iteration 3 Insights:**\n- Substring dedup rule was still problematic for multi-line joins\n- Position factor × threshold interaction excluded second titles on multi-recipe pages\n- Revealed that `rawScore` comparisons in dedup ignored structural bonuses earned by full joins\n\n---\n\n### Iterations 4-6: Structural Filtering & Bonuses (33.3% → 66.7%)\n\n**Major advances** in hard filters and structural heading detection:\n- Added metadata pattern filtering (SERVES, MAKES, YIELDS, etc.)\n- Implemented `isStructuralHeading()` to identify ALL_CAPS headings\n- Introduced ALL_CAPS bonus (+0.08) and structural heading bonus (+0.10)\n- Added position factor based on line position\n- Implemented continuation join protection for lines starting with `&`, `/`, `+`, `:`\n\n**Emerging Pattern:**\nTests passing stably: ARAYES SHRAK, FINNISH FLATBREADS, MIXED SEED CRISPBREAD, OVERNIGHT PIZZA DOUGH, PIEROGI RUSKIE (implied from later tests)\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 7: Failure Analysis on Remaining Cases (50% baseline)\n\n**Failures identified:**\n1. **Baked Eggs with Feta** → truncated (missing \"& Coriander\")\n   - Root cause: Continuation join scored below embedding threshold despite passing hard filters\n   - Embedding model penalizes ingredient-bearing titles (Feta, Harissa → similar to ingredient lists)\n   \n2. **CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM** → returned both the title AND sub-section header joined with \"+\"\n   - Root cause: Algorithm cannot distinguish sub-section headers from second recipe titles\n   - Multi-title guard fired on 2 ALL_CAPS candidates without checking if they're in same recipe\n   \n3. **Faszerowana papryka** → returned \"PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM\" (Korean romanization)\n   - Root cause: ALL_CAPS bonuses (+0.18 combined) override first-line mixed-case title\n   - Polish title had lower embedding similarity to English TITLE_REFERENCE\n   \n4. **SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS** → truncated/mismatched\n   - Issue A: OCR reads \"/\" but expected title has \":\" (evaluation harness issue)\n   - Issue B: 25-candidate pre-filter cuts the long 9-word join, keeping only partial 5-word version\n\n**Key Insights:**\n- Continuation joins are fragile (depend on long chain of conditions)\n- ALL_CAPS bias defeats mixed-case titles in bilingual recipes\n- Evaluation harness has separator normalization issues\n- Ground truth expectations can be impossible to match when OCR misreads characters\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 8: Implementing Structural Pre-Processing (75% → ?)\n\n**Planned fixes from Iteration 7:**\n1. **Pre-merge continuation lines** (before candidate generation) → direct fix for split titles\n2. **Ingredient-gap detection** in multi-title guard → distinguish section headers from second titles\n3. **First-line mixed-case protection** → prefer bilingual primary titles over romanizations\n4. **Eval harness fix** → normalize separators\n\n**Iteration 8 Results:**\n- 75% passing (6/8)\n- New failures introduced:\n\n**Failures in Iteration 8:**\n1. **Baked Eggs** → empty string `''`\n   - Pre-merge worked correctly, but embedding scorer rated ingredient-bearing title below threshold\n   - No fallback for unambiguous sole candidate\n   - \"Harissa Tomato Sauce\", \"Feta\", \"Coriander\" pulled embedding toward HEADER_REFERENCE\n   \n2. **Faszerowana papryka** → still \"PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM\"\n   - First-line protection condition too strict: requires candidate to survive threshold independently\n   - When ALL_CAPS bonuses inflate threshold, mixed-case title cannot reach it\n   - Protection never fires because precondition (both in `selected`) is violated\n\n**Key Realization:**\n- First-line protection is self-defeating: only works when mixed-case title doesn't need it\n- Empty candidate pool needs fallback to best positional candidate\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 9: Pre-Threshold Detection & Fallbacks (87.5% → ?)\n\n**Fixes implemented:**\n1. **Pre-threshold bilingual detection** → suppress ALL_CAPS subtitle before threshold calculation\n   - Moved from post-threshold to pre-threshold\n   - Used semantic similarity check (0.4 threshold) instead of just position + count\n   \n2. **Empty-pool fallback** → when threshold filters everything, return best positional candidate\n   - Safety net for embedding-penalized but structurally-valid titles\n\n**Iteration 9 Results:**\n- 87.5% passing (7/8)\n\n**Remaining Failure:**\n- **Faszerowana papryka** → still \"PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM\"\n\n**Root Cause of Failure:**\n- Bilingual detection condition `preAllCaps.length === 1` too strict\n- Polish recipes have additional ALL_CAPS lines: \"NA 3 PAPRYKI\" (serving size), \"SKŁADNIKI\" (ingredients), \"WARZYWA\" (vegetables)\n- When `preAllCaps.length === 4`, the suppression doesn't fire\n- ALL_CAPS romanization remains in scoring pool and wins via bonuses\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 10: Polish Metadata & Cross-Lingual Robustness (75% → ?)\n\n**Major fixes for Polish recipe patterns:**\n\n**Fix 1: Polish Metadata Patterns**\nAdded to `METADATA_PATTERNS`:\n- Serving sizes: `NA\\s+(\\d|OKOŁO)` (for N items), `DLA\\s+\\d` (for N people)\n- Time units: `\\d+\\s*MIN`, `\\d+\\s*GODZ` (catches OCR corruptions like PRZYGOTOWANTE, GOTOMANTE)\n\n**Fix 2: Pre-dedup Sub-section Header Removal**\n- Before dedup runs, identify and remove ALL_CAPS sub-section headers that are:\n  - Followed by ingredient-like content (strong sub-section signal)\n  - Substrings of longer candidates (conflict resolution)\n\n**Fix 3: Structural Heading Tiebreaker** (optional defense-in-depth)\n- When two structural headings have rawScores within 0.03 of each other:\n  - Prefer longer candidate (more specific = more likely actual title)\n  - If tied on length, prefer earlier position\n\n**Iteration 10 Results:**\n- 75% passing (6/8)\n- Two failures introduced (regressions):\n\n**Failures in Iteration 10:**\n1. **CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM** → returns `CHLEBEK`\n   - Root cause: 25-candidate pre-filter's \"short first\" sorting deprioritizes long titles\n   - \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\" (5 words, status at edge of `wordCount <= 5` boundary)\n   - But actually: structural heading mis-selection + dedup issue\n   \n2. **Faszerowana papryka** → still `PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM`\n   - \"NA 3 PAPRYKI\" survives hard filters (Polish pattern not in filters yet)\n   - Even with bilingual suppression, all-caps bonus on serving size beats mixed-case title\n\n**Correction issued:**\n- CHLEBEK title actually has exactly 5 words (not 6)\n- Real issue: `bestStructural` picks \"WARZYWA I BOCZEK\" instead of full title (cross-lingual embedding noise)\n- Prefix filter targets wrong heading, leaving `CHLEBEK` substring uncaught\n\n---\n\n### Iteration 11: Bilingual Detection Regression (87.5% → 87.5%, but with different failure)\n\n**Single Failure:**\n- **CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM** → returns `CHLEBEK`\n\n**Root Cause: Bilingual Detection False Positive**\n- Book category header \"Lato | Dania główne\" (Summer | Main dishes) at position 0 is mixed-case\n- Bilingual detector mistakes it for a recipe title\n- Compares it to \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\" at position 1\n- Food-domain terms share enough semantic space that similarity exceeds 0.4 threshold\n- Suppression removes the actual recipe title from threshold calculation\n- Downstream prefix removal and pre-dedup filters cannot act because full title missing from `selected`\n- Only \"CHLEBEK\" sub-section header survives\n\n**Key Insights from Iteration 11:**\n1. Book category headers at position 0 break bilingual detection (indistinguishable by position alone)\n2. 0.4 similarity threshold too permissive within food domain\n3. Multiple downstream safety mechanisms are gated on full title being in `selected`\n4. Section headers (WARZYWA, CHLEBEK) resemble recipe titles structurally (short, ALL_CAPS, food words)\n\n---\n\n## Recurring Patterns Across All Iterations\n\n### Pattern 1: Continuation Fragments Breaking Multi-Line Joins\n**Iterations affected**: 1, 2, 3, 7, 8\n- Lines starting with `&`, `/`, `+`, `:` are continuation lines\n- **Iteration 7 fix**: Pre-merge continuation lines before candidate generation\n- **Status after Iteration 8+**: Fixed (no longer failing)\n\n### Pattern 2: ALL_CAPS Bias Against Mixed-Case Bilingual Titles\n**Iterations affected**: 7, 8, 9, 10, 11\n- ALL_CAPS bonuses (+0.08) + structural bonus (+0.10) = +0.18 advantage\n- Overwhelms position factor (×1.12) for mixed-case first-line titles\n- **Iteration 9 fix**: Pre-threshold bilingual detection with semantic similarity validation\n- **Status**: Partially fixed; Iteration 11 shows false-positive edge case\n\n### Pattern 3: Polish Metadata Patterns Not Filtered\n**Iterations affected**: 9, 10, 11\n- Polish serving sizes: \"NA 3 PAPRYKI\", \"DLA 4 OSÓB\"\n- Polish time metadata: \"PRZYGOTOWANIE\", \"GOTOWANIE\", \"OCZEKIWANIE\" + durations\n- **Iteration 10 fix**: Added Polish patterns to `METADATA_PATTERNS`\n- **Status**: Fixed for Faszerowana papryka; CHLEBEK issue persists from other root\n\n### Pattern 4: Sub-Section Headers Defeating Dedup Logic\n**Iterations affected**: 1, 3, 7, 10, 11\n- Bread section \"CHLEBEK\", ingredient section \"WARZYWA I BOCZEK\" treated as candidate titles\n- Dedup rule \"shorter wins\" removes full title when sub-section is its substring\n- **Iteration 10 fix**: Pre-dedup filter removes ALL_CAPS sub-headers followed by ingredients\n- **Status**: Ineffective in Iteration 11 because full title already suppressed upstream\n\n### Pattern 5: Threshold Filtering Overruling Hard Filters\n**Iterations affected**: 1, 7, 8, 9\n- Candidates pass all structural filters but fall below embedding threshold\n- No fallback when sole/best candidate is discarded\n- **Iteration 9 fix**: Empty-pool fallback to best positional candidate when threshold filters all\n- **Status**: Fixed for Baked Eggs; doesn't help when wrong candidate suppressed upstream\n\n### Pattern 6: Cascading Dependency on Full Title Presence\n**Iterations affected**: 10, 11\n- Prefix removal (line 458) gated on `firstStructuralHeading in selected`\n- Pre-dedup filter (line 506) gated on longer parent in `selected`\n- Both fail simultaneously if full title suppressed upstream\n- **Status**: Design fragility; needs upstream fixes to prevent suppression\n\n### Pattern 7: Embedding Model Language Bias\n**Iterations affected**: 1, 7, 8, 9, 10, 11\n- MiniLM is English-centric\n- Polish titles \"Faszerowana papryka\", \"CHLEBEK\" embed poorly vs. English TITLE_REFERENCE\n- Cross-lingual mixing causes structural heading detection to pick wrong candidate\n- **Status**: Partially mitigated by bilingual detection; full solution would need multilingual embedding or language-agnostic scoring\n\n### Pattern 8: Distinguishing Section Headers from Recipe Titles Structurally\n**Iterations affected**: 7, 10, 11\n- Section headers: ALL_CAPS, 1-3 words, followed by ingredients\n- Recipe titles: ALL_CAPS, 3-5+ words, followed by body text\n- Multi-title guard checks for ingredients between titles to distinguish\n- **Status**: Works when both candidates present; fails when one suppressed upstream\n\n---\n\n## Test Input Evolution\n\n### Original Test Set (Iterations 1-6)\n1. **ARAYES SHRAK** — Split ALL_CAPS title across 2 short lines\n2. **Baked Eggs with Feta, Harissa Tomato Sauce & Coriander** — Mixed-case with ingredient words, split with `&` continuation\n3. **FINNISH MILK FLATBREADS + FINNISH POTATO FLATBREADS** — Multi-recipe page with 2 ALL_CAPS titles\n4. **MIXED SEED CRISPBREAD** — ALL_CAPS title buried under OCR garbage\n5. **OVERNIGHT STRAIGHT PIZZA DOUGH** — ALL_CAPS title with technique-oriented semantics\n6. **SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK : COTTAGE CHEESE (VARIATION D)** — Long split ALL_CAPS title with special characters\n\n### Extended Test Set (Iterations 7-11)\n7. **Faszerowana papryka** — Polish mixed-case title + ALL_CAPS Korean romanization (bilingual)\n8. (Unreleased in feedback) — Additional test in Iteration 11 suite\n\n### Untracked Inputs in Recent Iterations\n- Kimchi z ogórków\n- MŁODE PORY DUSZONE W PIWIE\n(Mentioned in Iteration 10 improvement plan as benefiting from Polish metadata patterns)\n\n---\n\n## Current Technical Debt & Edge Cases\n\n### Critical Edge Case (Iteration 11)\n- Book category headers at position 0 indistinguishable from recipe titles\n- Bilingual detection fires on category → actual title pair, suppressing real title\n- Requires either:\n  - Stricter position-2-only check (exclude position 0 from bilingual detection)\n  - Higher similarity threshold (e.g., 0.5+ instead of 0.4) to avoid food-domain false positives\n  - Category header recognition (look for `|` separator, metadata structure)\n\n### Fragile Dependency Chain\n1. Full title must survive pre-threshold suppression\n2. Prefix removal depends on it being in `selected`\n3. Pre-dedup filter depends on longer parent in `selected`\n4. Dedup rule depends on both being available for comparison\n5. Multi-title guard fallback only works if something survives\n\n**Fix needed**: Make downstream logic more robust to upstream suppression or add stronger upstream guards\n\n### Polish Language Support\n- Metadata patterns now covered (Iteration 10+)\n- But cross-lingual embedding quality still affects structural heading selection\n- CHLEBEK/WARZYWA conflict stems from `bestStructural` picking wrong heading via rawScore\n\n### Evaluation Harness Debt\n- SAFFRON case: OCR reads \"/\" but expected title has \":\" — impossible to match without separator normalization\n- Noted as out-of-scope for algorithm; resides in `title-loop.py`\n\n---\n\n## Summary Statistics\n\n| Metric | Iteration 1 | Iteration 11 | Notes |\n|--------|-----------|------------|-------|\n| **Accuracy** | 16.7% (1/6) | 87.5% (7/8) | +70.8 percentage points |\n| **Passing Tests** | 1 | 7 | All from original set survive |\n| **Failing Tests** | 5 | 1 | Only CHLEBEK fails |\n| **Root Causes Addressed** | 0 | 7+ | Continuation, metadata, bilingual detection, dedup, etc. |\n| **Known Regressions** | — | 1 | Bilingual detection false positive (Iteration 11) |\n| **Lines of Code (estimated)** | ~200 | ~500+ | Bonuses, filters, guards, fallbacks added |"}],"totalDurationMs":66192,"totalTokens":103632,"totalToolUseCount":18,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7541,"cache_read_input_tokens":91575,"output_tokens":4510,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":7541},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
