{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01FPVrpifqorDppKhTQmZco6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the context I need. Let me outline my key proposed changes and then write the improvement plan.\n\nThe single failure: **CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM** → returns `CHLEBEK`\n\nRoot cause chain:\n1. \"Lato | Dania główne\" at position 0 is a book category header, not a title\n2. Bilingual detection treats it as a mixed-case title and suppresses nearby ALL_CAPS candidates\n3. The real title \"CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM\" gets suppressed\n4. Downstream safety mechanisms all require the full title in `selected`, so they can't recover\n\n\n5. My approach is to fix this at the source: exclude category headers from bilingual detection, and add a guard to prevent suppressing structural headings that are almost certainly the recipe title.\n\nNow I'm testing whether fix #1 alone is sufficient. If the category header is excluded from bilingual detection, then the full recipe title stays in the candidate pool, gets the structural heading bonus, and the pre-dedup filter should catch the duplicate. But I'm also adding the other two fixes as safety nets—checking all candidates in the section filter rather than just selected ones, and protecting structural headings from suppression.\n\nLooking at the test cases, `|` only appears in \"Lato | Dania główne\", and recipe titles virtually never contain pipes, so this is a pretty safe pattern to exclude from bilingual detection. Though I should also consider whether other category headers at position 0 could trigger the same false positive in the future—that's where fix #2 comes in.\n\nThe cleanest solution is to treat `|` as a hard filter that removes lines from candidates entirely, since it's a structural separator rather than a continuation character like the ones already handled in pre-merge. Let me document this improvement plan.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5237,"cache_read_input_tokens":37804,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5237},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e5c8568-eb2f-4e0e-8771-787e6907f7e7","uuid":"92d7d959-3a79-4f7c-9ab1-363a0285d956"}
