{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01FPVrpifqorDppKhTQmZco6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a thorough understanding. Here's my analysis before writing the plan:\n\n**The single failure: CHLEBEK Z WARZYWAMI I BOCZKIEM → returns \"CHLEBEK\"**\n\nThree proposed changes, in decreasing priority:\n\n1. **Category header detection (Primary fix)**: \"Lato | Dania główne\" contains a `|` pipe separator — a hallmark of book category headers (\"Season | Category\") that recipe titles never use. Add this as a hard filter or at minimum exclude pipe-containing lines from bilingual detection's position-0 role. This single change unblocks the entire downstream chain.\n\n2. **Guard bilingual suppression against structural headings (Defense in depth)**: If bilingual detection would suppress a candidate that is also the `firstStructuralHeading`, skip suppression. The structural heading is the algorithm's highest-confidence title signal — letting a speculative bilingual heuristic override it is a design flaw that will recur with other inputs.\n\n3. **Make pre-dedup section filter check all candidates, not just `selected` (Defense in depth)**: The filter at lines 506-523 only removes \"CHLEBEK\" when a longer parent exists in `selected`. Broadening this to check `rawScored` means even if the full title is wrongly suppressed upstream, the section header \"CHLEBEK\" still gets removed because the full title exists as a known candidate."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5237,"cache_read_input_tokens":37804,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5237},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e5c8568-eb2f-4e0e-8771-787e6907f7e7","uuid":"4b4816c6-79dc-4a64-a8d4-ebf26ea59203"}
