{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01G8AGss7NhsSmTmE35MEB8s","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Written to `tools/title-loop/docs/11-023af39/improvement-plan.md`.\n\n**Key diagnosis:** The bilingual detection falsely fires because \"Lato | Dania główne\" (a book category header) at position 0 is mistaken for a mixed-case recipe title. This suppresses the real title, and every downstream safety mechanism is gated on it being present — so they all fail in cascade.\n\n**Three proposed fixes:**\n\n1. **Primary — Pipe filter in `passesHardFilters()`**: Lines with ` | ` are book category headers, never recipe titles. One line addition excludes them from candidates entirely, preventing the false trigger.\n\n2. **Defense in depth — Guard structural headings from bilingual suppression**: Never let bilingual detection suppress `firstStructuralHeading`. It's the algorithm's highest-confidence signal and shouldn't be overridden by a speculative heuristic.\n\n3. **Defense in depth — Broaden pre-dedup section filter**: Check `rawScored` instead of `selected` for longer parents, so the filter works even when the full title was suppressed upstream. Breaks the cascading dependency.\n\nFix A alone is sufficient for this input. All three together protect against the general class of \"upstream suppression leaves section headers as sole survivors.\""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4562,"cache_read_input_tokens":43041,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4562},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3e5c8568-eb2f-4e0e-8771-787e6907f7e7","uuid":"d0bf2e4a-86eb-42b6-8415-84ddaa17ed16"}
